WEBVTT

00:01.392 --> 00:04.265
[instrumental music]

00:40.997 --> 00:43.913
[instrumental music]

01:05.543 --> 01:07.632
[aircraft droning]

01:07.806 --> 01:10.679
[helicopters whirring]

01:31.047 --> 01:32.962
You know, staring at him
don't make it no easier, bro.

01:33.136 --> 01:34.398
Not gonna make it
no worse either.

01:34.572 --> 01:35.486
[Travis chuckling]

01:36.922 --> 01:37.880
[gunfire]

01:42.058 --> 01:43.973
We haven't been outside
the wire in, what, three weeks?

01:44.147 --> 01:46.323
Not a peep.

01:46.497 --> 01:49.239
Sounds like a devil's wedding
reception out there tonight.

01:49.413 --> 01:51.807
You alright, bro?

01:51.981 --> 01:55.202
'Cause I can talk to Ranger 6,
take your platoon out.

01:55.376 --> 01:58.074
No. I got this.

02:02.165 --> 02:04.733
You know,
TJ turns ten next month.

02:04.907 --> 02:07.910
- We're gonna get him baptized.
- That's cool, man.

02:08.084 --> 02:10.304
Tell him Uncle Travis says hello
when you call him, alright?

02:13.959 --> 02:15.918
Remember when this whole thing
got started, man?

02:17.876 --> 02:19.313
Just two young,
hard charging infantrymen

02:19.487 --> 02:20.879
ready to take on the world.

02:23.839 --> 02:25.275
Look at us now.

02:26.624 --> 02:28.757
Fifteen years later,

02:28.931 --> 02:32.064
and we're still fighting
this war.

02:32.239 --> 02:34.328
Don't know what you want me
to say about that, brother.

02:35.503 --> 02:36.808
Wanna drink this?

02:39.811 --> 02:42.205
Nothing you can say.
It is what it is.

02:45.339 --> 02:46.688
But I appreciate it if you pray
with me tonight, though,

02:46.862 --> 02:48.472
before I go outside the wire.

02:48.646 --> 02:50.605
No, now, we done went down
this rabbit hole

02:50.779 --> 02:52.259
tons of time, Preach, alright?

02:52.433 --> 02:53.521
You know I don't subscribe
to the lies

02:53.695 --> 02:55.436
in that book, alright?

02:55.610 --> 02:58.221
Plus, if God did exist,
He don't give a crap about me.

03:03.008 --> 03:07.622
This is, what, your eighth tour
in the last ten years?

03:07.796 --> 03:10.233
You received three purple
hearts, survived two IED attacks

03:10.407 --> 03:13.062
and you still don't believe
that not only does God exist,

03:13.236 --> 03:14.890
but He's got something bigger
in store for your life.

03:15.064 --> 03:17.022
War is my life, brother.

03:18.589 --> 03:20.417
That's what I do.

03:20.591 --> 03:21.810
That's all I know.

03:24.813 --> 03:27.163
I'll really appreciate
the extra coverage tonight.

03:27.337 --> 03:28.817
Ain't gonna happen, Preach.

03:34.823 --> 03:37.260
You know, this, this Bible
belonged to my grandfather.

03:39.262 --> 03:41.090
He gave it to my father
and my father gave it to me

03:41.264 --> 03:42.396
when I was about TJ's age.

03:42.570 --> 03:44.746
And just stop right there.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.704
If I was you, I'd make sure
the lies in that book

03:46.878 --> 03:49.316
don't get spread
throughout my family no more.

03:52.580 --> 03:55.496
You've lost your way, Travis.

03:55.670 --> 03:56.671
And worst part about that
is that

03:56.845 --> 03:59.630
you've lost your faith in God.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.980
Yeah, well...

04:02.154 --> 04:04.244
Did you ever think maybe
your God lost his faith in me?

04:04.418 --> 04:08.248
No! I don't, because He hasn't
and He never will.

04:10.380 --> 04:12.295
Preach, look, man.

04:12.469 --> 04:14.689
My parents spent
their whole lives chasing after

04:14.863 --> 04:18.083
the lies in that book, man,
and look where it got them.

04:18.258 --> 04:19.607
You need to go home, brother.

04:21.304 --> 04:22.827
You need to look
into your parents' accident.

04:23.001 --> 04:26.091
I know it's not gonna be easy,
but you need to move on.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.747
So what, Preach, is that what
your God telling me I should do?

04:29.921 --> 04:30.879
[gunfire]

04:31.053 --> 04:33.185
Your soul is lost, brother.

04:33.360 --> 04:36.145
You're lost.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.408
But it's never too late
to find your way back to God.

04:38.582 --> 04:41.759
The question is,
do you wanna find your way back?

04:42.673 --> 04:45.154
Man...

04:45.328 --> 04:47.635
Don't lose your life
without having your soul ready.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.115
Whatever, man.

04:51.465 --> 04:52.640
Preach: Travis.

04:54.206 --> 04:56.252
Am I my brother's keeper?

04:56.426 --> 04:58.036
Stay alert, Preach.

05:01.388 --> 05:02.824
Stay alive, brother.

05:06.784 --> 05:08.133
Stay alive.

05:08.308 --> 05:10.005
[instrumental music]

05:11.789 --> 05:14.183
Sarge! Sarge!
Get up! It's second platoon!

05:14.357 --> 05:15.750
Man 1: They just got hit!
- What?

05:15.924 --> 05:17.491
Man 1: The second platoon.
They just got hit.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.188
How bad it is?
How many people got hurt?

05:19.362 --> 05:22.104
They're dead.
All of them, sarge.

05:22.974 --> 05:24.498
Oh, sh...

05:24.672 --> 05:27.065
Make a hole! Make a hole!
Make a hole!

05:27.239 --> 05:29.807
[siren blaring]

05:29.981 --> 05:31.287
Bring him right here! Right
here! Right here! Let's go!

05:31.461 --> 05:33.202
I need another hand, let's go!

05:33.376 --> 05:36.292
[dramatic music]

05:39.077 --> 05:41.166
No! No, no! No!

05:41.341 --> 05:44.039
Oh. Oh. Oh!

05:44.213 --> 05:46.650
[sobbing] No, no, no!

05:46.824 --> 05:50.828
No! No! No! No! No!

05:51.002 --> 05:51.960
Shit!

06:01.622 --> 06:02.927
Preach, man.

06:04.146 --> 06:07.018
[instrumental music]

06:20.989 --> 06:23.383
[indistinct chatter]

06:25.602 --> 06:27.474
Hood: It's good to see you.
How there, Judy?

06:27.648 --> 06:29.084
- How's that grandbaby?
- Wonderful.

06:29.258 --> 06:31.434
[Hood chuckling]

06:31.608 --> 06:33.958
- Deacon Tiffany.
- Good morning, pastor.

06:34.132 --> 06:35.656
- Good to see you.
- Mwah. You, too.

06:35.830 --> 06:37.005
How are those
counseling sessions going?

06:37.179 --> 06:38.789
[sighing]
They are going so well,

06:38.963 --> 06:40.791
but you know
that we have got to...

06:40.965 --> 06:42.358
I know what you're going to say.

06:42.532 --> 06:44.012
I promise, as soon as the church
can afford it,

06:44.186 --> 06:45.317
we're gonna take care
of those repairs.

06:45.492 --> 06:46.623
- Yes, sir. Okay.
- Okay.

06:46.797 --> 06:48.016
- I'll see you later.
- Yes.

06:48.190 --> 06:49.757
- Hello there, Julie.
- Good morning.

06:49.931 --> 06:52.412
Why do we act surprised
when we're faced with trials?

06:53.891 --> 06:55.937
Hm?

06:56.111 --> 06:58.592
Why do we think
our trials and our problems

06:58.766 --> 07:02.030
are too big for us to handle
when we have God?

07:03.814 --> 07:05.860
Did He not say to us,
"Behold, I am the Lord,

07:06.034 --> 07:07.165
the God of all flesh."

07:07.339 --> 07:09.167
"Is anything too difficult
for Me?"

07:09.341 --> 07:12.214
Congregation: No. No!

07:12.388 --> 07:15.522
In Isaiah 41 and 10,
God tells us to not fear,

07:15.696 --> 07:17.349
for He is with us.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.917
In Psalms 55 and 22,

07:20.091 --> 07:23.181
He tells us
to cast our burdens upon Him,

07:23.355 --> 07:26.402
and He will sustain us.

07:26.576 --> 07:29.187
Just because we think
our trials and our problems

07:29.361 --> 07:32.103
are too big for us,
that does not make them

07:32.277 --> 07:33.627
too big for our God.

07:33.801 --> 07:34.845
[applauding]

07:35.019 --> 07:37.500
Amen.

07:37.674 --> 07:39.371
Hood: Even with everything
that's happening

07:39.546 --> 07:43.245
in our world today, all
the craziness that's going on,

07:43.419 --> 07:45.639
I want you to know
that God will build

07:45.813 --> 07:48.859
a mighty, mighty shield
around you

07:49.033 --> 07:51.340
if you trust and believe in Him.

07:52.994 --> 07:56.214
He will deliver you
because He is faithful

07:56.388 --> 07:58.521
and He is righteous.

07:58.695 --> 08:02.046
He is our El Shaddai,
our Lord God Almighty!

08:02.220 --> 08:04.701
He is Yahweh.

08:04.875 --> 08:07.487
He is El Olam,
our most high God!

08:07.661 --> 08:11.621
He is Jehovah-Jireh,
the Lord that provides.

08:11.795 --> 08:14.929
He is Jehovah-Rapha,
the Lord that heals.

08:17.105 --> 08:21.283
And I say that if you don't
know Him by any other name,

08:21.457 --> 08:23.851
you can take comfort
in knowing that He is

08:24.025 --> 08:26.810
and shall always be El-o-him.

08:26.984 --> 08:29.204
He is God!

08:29.378 --> 08:33.077
Amen! Amen!
That's right. Amen!

08:33.251 --> 08:37.517
Amen. Amen. Amen.

08:45.133 --> 08:48.005
[instrumental music]

09:08.635 --> 09:11.551
[music continues]

09:41.711 --> 09:44.584
[music continues]

10:10.479 --> 10:12.873
Big D: That looked like your boy
right there.

10:13.047 --> 10:16.137
Big Six: Yeah,
look at this clown.

10:16.311 --> 10:17.834
Big D: I guarantee you
he don't have the money.

10:18.008 --> 10:19.619
I bet he's short.

10:19.793 --> 10:22.665
Big Six: Think so?
Big D: I already know so.

10:27.931 --> 10:29.803
[window whirring]

10:33.023 --> 10:34.329
That's all we can afford.

10:36.548 --> 10:38.376
Feels light.

10:38.550 --> 10:41.728
You're gonna short me again
this month, too, huh?

10:41.902 --> 10:44.339
Feel that, Big D.
That feel light to you?

10:46.471 --> 10:49.387
And you got two weeks,
Sweat Suit Donnie.

10:49.561 --> 10:51.520
We can't pay that kind of money
to keep the shop open.

10:51.694 --> 10:54.479
Nah. That's where you're wrong.

10:54.654 --> 10:56.656
Everybody pays.

10:56.830 --> 10:59.876
And one way or the other,
everybody pays.

11:00.050 --> 11:01.008
[engine starts]

11:02.531 --> 11:03.619
I want my money, Donnie.

11:03.793 --> 11:06.056
[instrumental music]

11:06.230 --> 11:07.797
♪ I'mma show you
how to do this ♪♪♪

11:07.971 --> 11:10.365
[rap music]

11:17.894 --> 11:19.156
Water poured through the roof

11:19.330 --> 11:22.464
like a screen door
on a submarine.

11:22.638 --> 11:25.467
And that ain't the worst of it,
pastor.

11:25.641 --> 11:27.817
Hood: Oh, boy.

11:27.991 --> 11:30.864
[water splashing]

11:39.307 --> 11:42.266
Yo, yo, hold up, hold up!
Slow down. Slow down.

11:44.704 --> 11:47.924
There you go. [chuckles]

11:48.098 --> 11:49.970
Well, I'll be...

11:50.144 --> 11:51.014
What's up, Pop?

11:51.188 --> 11:53.625
[both laughing]

11:53.800 --> 11:55.279
When did you get home, son?

11:55.453 --> 11:57.934
I just got back yesterday.

11:58.108 --> 11:59.588
I was wondering when you was
gonna make it back this way,

11:59.762 --> 12:00.937
check on your parents' house.

12:01.111 --> 12:02.722
Uh, you know,
hell, I was coming.

12:02.896 --> 12:04.636
I just, uh, I just, I needed
a little time, you know,

12:04.811 --> 12:05.855
with the accident
and everything,

12:06.029 --> 12:07.683
just get my head together.

12:07.857 --> 12:10.077
Well, we, we all miss
your mom and dad.

12:10.251 --> 12:11.731
Yeah, I appreciate
you taking care of the place

12:11.905 --> 12:13.254
for me while I was gone.

12:13.428 --> 12:14.472
I just wish
that was the only reason

12:14.646 --> 12:16.561
I was coming back.

12:16.736 --> 12:18.389
Yeah, good friend of mine

12:18.563 --> 12:21.436
got killed last week
during a mission.

12:21.610 --> 12:24.265
His body is due back stateside
in a couple of weeks, so...

12:24.439 --> 12:27.529
Hm, escort duty.

12:27.703 --> 12:31.751
Yeah. This war has taken too
many of our good men and women.

12:31.925 --> 12:33.056
Pops, you know what,
to be honest, I don't even know

12:33.230 --> 12:35.015
if I can do it.
I don't know if I...

12:35.189 --> 12:37.147
To face 'em,
his family, his son.

12:37.321 --> 12:39.149
Oh, just lean on the Lord, son.

12:39.323 --> 12:41.021
He'll give you and his family
the strength

12:41.195 --> 12:43.414
to get through this,
yes, He will.

12:45.373 --> 12:46.896
Pops, how's business?
Where's Donnie?

12:47.070 --> 12:50.291
Hm, where's Donnie?
He's late. He's always late.

12:50.465 --> 12:51.988
I'm telling you,
one day that boy gonna be late

12:52.162 --> 12:54.251
for something either
very important or very bad.

12:54.425 --> 12:57.820
Don't know which, but I do know
for certain he will be late.

12:57.994 --> 12:59.430
[both laughing]

12:59.604 --> 13:00.954
- Same old Donnie, man.
- Same old.

13:01.128 --> 13:02.172
- Same old Donnie.
- Ah.

13:02.346 --> 13:04.174
As for business, well,

13:04.348 --> 13:06.829
the neighborhood's changed
since you were last here.

13:07.003 --> 13:09.919
- How so?
- Yeah, these kids.

13:10.093 --> 13:12.008
They're gonna be coming around
with pants hanging down

13:12.182 --> 13:16.317
to their ankles,
cursing and loud music,

13:16.491 --> 13:18.014
run all the customers off.

13:18.188 --> 13:19.711
- Who running off the customers?
- He expect me to--

13:19.886 --> 13:21.278
Oh, Pop, hold up, if you got
a problem with somebody,

13:21.452 --> 13:23.019
you know you can tell me,
I'm here now.

13:23.193 --> 13:24.673
- I'll take care of it.
- No, no, no.

13:24.847 --> 13:26.501
I can handle
these new-age gangsters.

13:26.675 --> 13:30.287
Plus, the Lord got a hedge
of protection around me 24/7.

13:30.461 --> 13:32.550
Yes, sir. [laughing]

13:32.724 --> 13:36.293
- Same old Pops.
- Um, hey, listen.

13:36.467 --> 13:38.165
When you take care of my
parents' house, did you ever--

13:38.339 --> 13:40.254
[dishes clattering]

13:40.428 --> 13:45.041
And it's also harder to get
good help these days.

13:45.215 --> 13:46.521
Alright, listen.
We need to take care of that.

13:46.695 --> 13:49.698
Yeah.
Let me go take control to that.

13:49.872 --> 13:52.135
- Alright.
- Listen.

13:52.309 --> 13:54.181
- Good to have you home, son.
- Good to be back.

13:54.355 --> 13:55.660
- Hm.
- It's good to be back.

13:55.835 --> 13:56.836
Just let me know
if you need anything.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.359
- Absolutely.
- Alright.

13:58.533 --> 14:00.187
Pops, Pops, Pops.

14:00.361 --> 14:02.450
- Rangers lead the way, Pops.
- Hoo-ah!

14:02.624 --> 14:04.931
Rangers lead the way! Yes, sir!

14:05.105 --> 14:06.019
[Travis chuckling]

14:11.459 --> 14:15.376
- War hero!
- Oh, man. Sweat Suit Donnie.

14:15.550 --> 14:17.204
- What's up, boy?
- How's it going, brother?

14:17.378 --> 14:18.596
- I'm good.
- When did you get back?

14:18.770 --> 14:20.033
Oh, I just got back yesterday,
man.

14:20.207 --> 14:21.773
Yeah.
How long are you in town for?

14:21.948 --> 14:23.688
- Two, maybe three weeks.
- Alright, listen. Listen.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.865
I'm late, but you already know
that, alright, but I'mma

14:26.039 --> 14:27.388
pick you up later, we're gonna
go shoot some pool together.

14:27.562 --> 14:29.259
Oh, man,
I can't do it tonight, man.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.435
I'm still tired from this trip,
man. Been in plane all day.

14:31.609 --> 14:33.089
Yeah, alright. Sure. Listen,
why don't you just come back?

14:33.263 --> 14:35.135
Inside for a coffee,
we can have doughnut--

14:35.309 --> 14:37.528
Maybe tomorrow, man, I got
something I gotta look into...

14:37.702 --> 14:39.443
You need some help?
I mean, I can tell Pops to--

14:39.617 --> 14:41.750
Bro! I promise you, I'll catch
up with you, alright?

14:41.924 --> 14:43.230
You late, you need to get in
there, I got something

14:43.404 --> 14:45.058
I gotta do, but we'll hang, man,
for sure.

14:45.232 --> 14:46.146
Alright.

14:48.496 --> 14:51.107
Possum's on the stump
with this one, pastor.

14:51.281 --> 14:52.804
Can it even be repaired?

14:52.979 --> 14:56.286
It can, but not by the boys
in this house.

14:56.460 --> 14:59.202
They about as useful
as a steering wheel on a mule.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.990
Alright, Pedie, just do
what you can to keep it running

15:04.164 --> 15:05.513
until I get something
figured out, alright?

15:05.687 --> 15:08.168
I'll do my best, pastor.
I'll do my best.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.473
I know you will.

15:12.172 --> 15:15.044
[siren blaring]

15:16.437 --> 15:19.092
[instrumental music]

15:20.876 --> 15:24.097
Woman on PA: Paging Dr. Benzer.
Paging Dr. Benzer.

15:28.318 --> 15:31.321
- Travis.
- Hey, Dr. Cunningham.

15:31.495 --> 15:33.280
- Welcome home.
- Thank you. Appreciate it.

15:33.454 --> 15:34.542
Thanks for taking the time
to see me.

15:34.716 --> 15:36.239
- What can I do for you?
- Look.

15:36.413 --> 15:38.415
I wanna talk to you
about my parents' accident.

15:38.589 --> 15:40.765
Yes. That's very unfortunate.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.159
I was going through their
belongings and I couldn't find

15:43.333 --> 15:45.205
this necklace
that I made for my mother.

15:45.379 --> 15:47.294
Are you sure she was wearing it
the night of the accident?

15:47.468 --> 15:51.037
Yeah, absolutely.
This is it right here.

15:51.211 --> 15:52.647
I'm just hoping
maybe somebody saw something.

15:52.821 --> 15:54.518
I'm-- I'm sorry.

15:54.692 --> 15:56.607
But I would have definitely
remembered that necklace.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.348
Are you sure?
I mean, you know...

15:58.522 --> 16:00.742
Maybe somebody from the staff,
maybe missed it or--

16:00.916 --> 16:03.701
Travis, all the belongings
that were on your parents

16:03.875 --> 16:06.966
when the paramedics brought them
in were carefully collected

16:07.140 --> 16:09.969
and cataloged and turned over
to the detectives.

16:10.143 --> 16:14.451
I-- I'm sorry, but that necklace
was not one of them.

16:16.453 --> 16:17.977
Woman on PA:
Dr. Cunningham to pharmacy.

16:18.151 --> 16:19.848
Dr. Cunningham to pharmacy.

16:20.022 --> 16:21.850
I've got to run.

16:22.024 --> 16:24.853
- It's good to see you.
- You, too. Thanks again.

16:25.027 --> 16:27.943
[instrumental music]

16:33.775 --> 16:36.691
[water sloshing]

16:49.878 --> 16:52.794
[metal clanking]

16:57.929 --> 16:58.887
Pull the gun!

17:01.324 --> 17:02.151
I'm gonna get my team,
we're gonna

17:02.325 --> 17:03.326
come around west, alright?

17:05.111 --> 17:08.027
[horn honking]

17:12.553 --> 17:15.425
[intense music]

17:17.079 --> 17:18.559
[gunfire]

17:18.733 --> 17:20.213
[screaming]

17:22.128 --> 17:23.955
Coming down the road
two sniper fire.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.957
[panting]

17:26.132 --> 17:29.048
[screaming]

17:34.314 --> 17:36.098
[sobbing]

17:40.059 --> 17:41.016
Ah!

17:52.636 --> 17:54.856
[indistinct chatter]

17:56.423 --> 17:57.815
Not as good as you could,
you know?

17:57.989 --> 17:59.730
[indistinct chatter]

18:02.646 --> 18:03.995
Who's there?

18:04.170 --> 18:06.650
Good evening, Pops.

18:06.824 --> 18:07.869
What do you want?

18:10.785 --> 18:12.091
It's a nice night.

18:13.179 --> 18:14.571
Pops: Who sent you?

18:14.745 --> 18:17.487
Damon: That's a real nice dress,
Ms. Wanda.

18:17.661 --> 18:20.621
- Go inside, lock the door.
- I will call the police.

18:24.886 --> 18:26.322
[door unlocking]

18:26.496 --> 18:27.802
I don't know what you want,
young man,

18:27.976 --> 18:31.022
but you, you making
a big mistake.

18:34.591 --> 18:38.117
Have a nice night... Pops.

18:47.213 --> 18:51.478
It was good to get that
off my chest. It felt strong.

18:51.652 --> 18:53.393
S-- strong?

18:53.567 --> 18:56.004
You air-force type don't know
anything about strong.

18:56.178 --> 18:58.224
This is army strong right here.

18:58.398 --> 19:00.748
You call that a gun?
This is a real gun.

19:00.922 --> 19:02.880
Courtesy,
United States Marine Corps.

19:03.054 --> 19:06.101
- You're all welcome.
- Here we go.

19:06.275 --> 19:08.930
We gotta listen to this
Marine Corps garbage again.

19:09.104 --> 19:11.324
Well, okay, on that note,

19:11.498 --> 19:14.849
I think that
that is all for now.

19:15.023 --> 19:18.548
You all have
a wonderful evening. Goodnight.

19:18.722 --> 19:20.550
All: Goodnight!

19:20.724 --> 19:23.597
[indistinct chatter]

19:27.340 --> 19:28.950
[sighing]

19:29.124 --> 19:32.258
- Did Pastor Hood stop by?
- He sure did.

19:32.432 --> 19:35.391
Roof's still leaking.
Temperature's still rising.

19:35.565 --> 19:37.001
AC is still broken.

19:37.176 --> 19:40.831
[sighing]
I will talk to him again.

19:41.005 --> 19:42.572
You do that, Ms. Tiffany,

19:42.746 --> 19:44.966
'cause if we don't get somebody
out here that can fix

19:45.140 --> 19:48.361
all these repairs,
especially that AC soon,

19:48.535 --> 19:50.319
it's going to get hotter
than two hamsters

19:50.493 --> 19:53.496
fighting in a wool sack.
Goodnight, doc.

19:57.152 --> 19:59.110
[dramatic music]

20:00.851 --> 20:03.811
[panting] Preach,
I'm taking the platoon now.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.291
I'm taking the platoon now.

20:05.465 --> 20:07.075
Sniper!

20:07.249 --> 20:09.382
Preach, no! No!

20:23.265 --> 20:26.181
[engine revving]

20:40.891 --> 20:43.851
He sent that man to our house.

20:44.025 --> 20:45.766
Poor mother is scared to death.

20:47.420 --> 20:48.638
I'll talk to him.

20:48.812 --> 20:51.162
You need to do
more than just talk.

20:52.860 --> 20:55.602
[sighs] Listen,
you got to fix this

20:55.776 --> 20:58.169
even if it means
telling him everything.

21:13.794 --> 21:16.187
[birds chirping]

21:17.450 --> 21:20.322
[instrumental music]

21:22.759 --> 21:25.632
[machine whirring]

21:29.113 --> 21:32.160
Don't even act like
you don't know what time it is!

21:32.334 --> 21:34.249
[laughing] Look at you, man,
come on.

21:34.423 --> 21:36.382
My brother, man. [laughing]

21:36.556 --> 21:37.426
[Travis laughing]

21:37.600 --> 21:40.951
Oh, man. Hm. Hm.

21:41.125 --> 21:44.085
Remember when we were little,
we used to make my parents stop

21:44.259 --> 21:45.565
every time
we saw a doughnut shop?

21:45.739 --> 21:46.914
I remember
you used to make them stop,

21:47.088 --> 21:48.481
I didn't used to make them stop.

21:48.655 --> 21:50.700
- Oh! So you complaining?
- No, you don't.

21:50.874 --> 21:52.398
[Donnie laughing]

21:52.572 --> 21:54.225
I still see you trying to be
of service

21:54.400 --> 21:56.750
and act like
you know how to fix stuff.

21:56.924 --> 21:58.491
I could use some help.
You wanna pick up a tool?

21:58.665 --> 22:02.712
Nope. No. I'll leave the manual
labor to you and dad.

22:02.886 --> 22:05.498
All that Rangers lead the way
and hoo-ah stuff,

22:05.672 --> 22:09.328
I'm like, "Rangers lead the way,
to where? Wh-- what's a hoo-ah?"

22:09.502 --> 22:11.547
I'mma have to school you
about that, man.

22:11.721 --> 22:14.681
- Man, good old times, man.
Travis: Yes, sir.

22:14.855 --> 22:17.336
I still remember your parents,
man.

22:17.510 --> 22:19.425
They didn't deserve to go
the way they did.

22:19.599 --> 22:21.557
Don't be sorry about it, man.

22:21.731 --> 22:24.908
Accidents happen
to good people, too.

22:25.082 --> 22:27.650
Speaking of good people,

22:27.824 --> 22:29.304
Pops looked a little rattled
yesterday, man.

22:29.478 --> 22:31.828
Everything alright in the shop?

22:32.002 --> 22:33.264
Cool as can be.

22:35.266 --> 22:37.225
Everything's cool, man.
I promise.

22:37.399 --> 22:38.400
Alright.

22:41.055 --> 22:43.362
I went to talk to Dr. Cunningham
yesterday.

22:43.536 --> 22:45.451
Donnie: And what's up?

22:45.625 --> 22:47.757
Man, it's this accident,

22:47.931 --> 22:50.804
look, none of them makes sense
to me, man. Never has.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.936
What do you mean?

22:53.110 --> 22:54.764
Donnie, my father would not have
just accelerated

22:54.938 --> 22:56.679
into a parked truck, man,

22:56.853 --> 23:00.030
unless somebody or someone or
something made him do that, man,

23:00.204 --> 23:01.902
caused him to react that way.

23:02.076 --> 23:04.078
Look, man, it was a ugly night
that night, Travis. Okay?

23:04.252 --> 23:06.863
There was a bad storm,
roads was wet, slick.

23:07.037 --> 23:08.387
Look, but you know my old man.

23:08.561 --> 23:09.823
I mean, that would have made him
more alert, man.

23:09.997 --> 23:11.302
He would have been sharp.

23:11.477 --> 23:13.087
I'm telling you,
all these slick roads

23:13.261 --> 23:17.526
and bad-night stuff people
keep saying, I ain't buying it.

23:17.700 --> 23:20.529
I think something else
was the cause.

23:20.703 --> 23:21.965
What do you think happened?

23:23.227 --> 23:25.534
You know what? I don't know.

23:25.708 --> 23:27.667
But I promise you,
I'm gonna find out.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.626
And when I do...

23:35.892 --> 23:37.024
Come on, man.

23:38.155 --> 23:41.071
[engine revving]

23:48.470 --> 23:51.386
[instrumental music]

24:15.192 --> 24:17.804
We've identified
three more homeless vets,

24:17.978 --> 24:19.414
but we can't bring them
into the center

24:19.588 --> 24:21.111
until the repairs are done.

24:21.285 --> 24:23.287
[sighs] We only have half
of what we need

24:23.462 --> 24:25.072
for all the repairs,

24:25.246 --> 24:28.379
and that's not even enough
to fix or replace the AC.

24:28.554 --> 24:31.470
- We have to do something.
- I know.

24:34.995 --> 24:37.040
Hood: Hey.
- Huh?

24:37.214 --> 24:40.479
What if we are supposed to get
another soldier to help us?

24:40.653 --> 24:42.872
I heard that Matthew Fox's son
is in town.

24:43.046 --> 24:46.180
And if I remember correctly, he
could fix just about anything.

24:46.354 --> 24:48.487
Well, do you think
he will help us?

24:48.661 --> 24:51.664
There's only one way
to find out. Let's go.

24:51.838 --> 24:52.752
Okay.

24:56.712 --> 24:59.193
[hammering]

24:59.367 --> 25:01.238
Hood: What did I tell you?
Tiffany: Heh-heh.

25:01.412 --> 25:02.762
Hood: Travis!

25:04.024 --> 25:04.938
Hello!

25:06.766 --> 25:08.637
- How you doing, pastor?
Hood: Doing good.

25:08.811 --> 25:11.161
It's good to see you here safe
and in good health.

25:11.335 --> 25:12.815
To God be all the glory.

25:14.774 --> 25:16.602
Let me tell you something,
I really,

25:16.776 --> 25:18.865
really miss your mom and dad.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.780
They were fine, fine people.

25:22.477 --> 25:24.610
Travis,
this is Tiffany Robinson.

25:24.784 --> 25:27.047
She heads up our new
Veterans Center Ministry.

25:27.221 --> 25:29.049
Hi.

25:29.223 --> 25:31.225
What can I do for you, pastor?

25:31.399 --> 25:34.315
Well, it's the veteran's center
building.

25:34.489 --> 25:37.797
- It's in pretty bad shape.
- It's in horrible shape.

25:37.971 --> 25:39.712
[laughing]

25:39.886 --> 25:41.278
She's right.

25:41.452 --> 25:43.324
Travis, we need someone
with your skills

25:43.498 --> 25:45.108
who can come in and help us
renovate this place,

25:45.282 --> 25:47.502
so that we can open our doors
for veterans like you

25:47.676 --> 25:49.939
who need our help.

25:50.113 --> 25:51.767
Do I look like I need your help?

25:55.118 --> 25:56.293
I didn't quite mean it
like that--

25:56.467 --> 25:58.687
Can't do it, alright?

25:58.861 --> 26:00.341
I got a lot of work
to get done here.

26:00.515 --> 26:01.429
Plus, there's something
I need to check into

26:01.603 --> 26:03.518
before I report back, so...

26:03.692 --> 26:06.129
[sighing] I'm sorry, alright?

26:06.303 --> 26:08.044
I'm sorry you had to come all
the way out here for nothing.

26:08.218 --> 26:10.264
So, so that's it?

26:10.438 --> 26:12.701
You're gonna turn your back
on us just like that?

26:12.875 --> 26:13.833
Yeah.

26:14.007 --> 26:14.877
Is it that easy for you

26:15.051 --> 26:16.618
to turn your back on God?

26:19.273 --> 26:20.535
[intense music]

26:20.709 --> 26:23.103
Turn my back on God?

26:23.277 --> 26:26.106
You cannot be serious right now,
'cause the way I see it,

26:26.280 --> 26:27.977
God turned his back on me
a long time ago!

26:28.151 --> 26:29.849
That is not true, Travis.
God loves you.

26:30.023 --> 26:32.808
He loves me? Just what exactly
has God done for me?

26:32.982 --> 26:36.116
More than any of us can even
imagine, not the least of which

26:36.290 --> 26:38.118
was dying for your sins
and answering your prayers.

26:38.292 --> 26:41.077
My prayers. Y'all always talking
about prayers.

26:41.251 --> 26:44.385
You know who else pray?
Enemy soldiers.

26:44.559 --> 26:48.128
Enemy soldiers pray
all the time, 10-20 times a day.

26:48.302 --> 26:50.565
But do you know what they do
when they finish praying?

26:50.739 --> 26:52.698
Do you?

26:52.872 --> 26:56.266
They strap on explosives
and they kill Americans!

26:56.440 --> 26:57.572
My friends!

26:57.746 --> 26:58.617
And for what?

26:58.791 --> 27:00.793
Some stupid religion?

27:00.967 --> 27:03.143
But that's,
that's not God's work.

27:03.317 --> 27:05.885
No? It ain't God's work,
then whose is it?

27:06.059 --> 27:07.800
What? Satan's?

27:07.974 --> 27:09.410
Oh, so what, God's taken
a coffee break now, alright?

27:09.584 --> 27:11.325
- He ain't calling the shots?
- Travis.

27:11.499 --> 27:15.024
Regardless of the circumstances,
God still loves you.

27:15.198 --> 27:16.809
- He loves me.
- He loves us all.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.985
"He loves us all?
He loves me. He loves us all!"

27:19.159 --> 27:20.987
What about
Staff Sergeant Pearson, huh?

27:21.161 --> 27:22.728
An IED ripped through
his vehicle

27:22.902 --> 27:24.730
and ripped him into pieces!

27:24.904 --> 27:27.863
Or what about Corporal Wilson?
Must've really loved him.

27:28.037 --> 27:31.258
Sniper bullet nearly took
half his head off.

27:31.432 --> 27:33.652
And I guess God really loved
Preach, He got a funny way

27:33.826 --> 27:35.697
of showing love to Preach
'cause He let a 500-pound

27:35.871 --> 27:38.569
roadside bomb
tear him to pieces,

27:38.744 --> 27:40.441
cut his whole platoon down!

27:42.051 --> 27:43.705
Or what about my mom
and my daddy?

27:46.665 --> 27:49.624
God can help you, Travis.

27:49.798 --> 27:52.322
I don't need your help,
I don't need your help,

27:52.496 --> 27:54.890
and I definitely don't need His.

27:55.064 --> 27:58.807
What I need is for you and you
to get off my property, now.

27:58.981 --> 28:00.113
Just go.

28:05.466 --> 28:06.510
You're gonna find
your way back to God.

28:06.685 --> 28:08.730
I said, get off!

28:08.904 --> 28:11.341
Pastor, it's time for us to go.
It's time to go.

28:13.996 --> 28:15.128
Come on, pastor.

28:20.437 --> 28:23.136
[gunfire]

28:23.310 --> 28:25.007
- What we got?
- Coming down the road!

28:25.181 --> 28:27.270
Two sniper fire
and then a guy down over there!

28:27.444 --> 28:28.924
Alright, copy that, copy that!

28:29.098 --> 28:31.448
I'mma grab my team!
We're gonna go on rounds!

28:31.622 --> 28:33.276
- Hey, come with us, okay?
- Okay.

28:33.450 --> 28:36.366
[gunfire]

28:37.803 --> 28:38.760
[grunting]

28:42.938 --> 28:44.723
[screaming]

28:44.897 --> 28:46.159
Really appreciate it if you
pray with me tonight, though,

28:46.333 --> 28:47.856
before I go outside the wire.

28:48.030 --> 28:49.597
I could really use
your extra coverage tonight.

28:49.771 --> 28:50.685
Ain't gonna happen, Preach.

28:50.859 --> 28:52.078
[screaming]

29:01.000 --> 29:03.872
[engine revving]

29:07.006 --> 29:09.138
[panting]

29:25.894 --> 29:27.243
Preach: They're right, you know?

29:29.680 --> 29:31.291
God don't love me, Preach.

29:34.120 --> 29:35.643
Why are you doing this
to yourself?

29:35.817 --> 29:37.384
'Cause I could have done
something.

29:39.299 --> 29:40.866
I should have talked to Ranger 6
into letting your platoon

29:41.040 --> 29:42.693
out that night.

29:42.868 --> 29:44.783
And you would be dead now
instead of me.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.005
I don't know what to do, Preach.

29:50.179 --> 29:51.572
You can always go to God.

29:53.443 --> 29:55.358
God can't save me, man.

29:55.532 --> 29:58.318
God is our rescuer, Travis.

29:58.492 --> 30:01.712
He's granted us eternal life.

30:01.887 --> 30:03.453
But we can't allow our sins
to keep us from Him,

30:03.627 --> 30:05.891
'cause if we do,
it causes Him to reject us

30:06.065 --> 30:07.893
and not listen to our prayers.

30:08.067 --> 30:09.764
But I shouldn't even
be here, man.

30:11.070 --> 30:12.593
I should be over there.

30:12.767 --> 30:15.422
I should be helping
our brothers.

30:15.596 --> 30:17.685
In fact, why am I still alive
and you're not?

30:19.905 --> 30:22.385
You're still alive
because God has a plan for you.

30:24.431 --> 30:26.433
There's something important
you still have to do.

30:28.043 --> 30:31.133
Preach, what's that even mean,
man? Uh...

30:31.307 --> 30:33.048
[sobbing]

30:33.222 --> 30:34.745
Preach: Stay alert, Travis.

30:40.577 --> 30:41.796
Stay alive.

30:44.407 --> 30:45.321
Stay alive.

30:47.193 --> 30:49.238
Are you okay, sir?

30:49.412 --> 30:51.850
[indistinct radio chatter]

30:53.808 --> 30:55.854
Yeah. [sniffling]

30:57.464 --> 30:59.727
I'm fine.

30:59.901 --> 31:01.468
Just got a little winded,
alright?

31:01.642 --> 31:06.212
- Sir, can we see some ID?
- I was jogging, alright?

31:06.386 --> 31:08.518
I ain't got no ID. I ain't doing
nothing, I'm just--

31:08.692 --> 31:12.566
Sir, get your hands out of your
pocket and get on the ground.

31:12.740 --> 31:14.960
I was just jogging.
Why are you all on me?

31:15.134 --> 31:16.744
Sir, get your hands
out of your pocket

31:16.918 --> 31:18.746
and get on the ground now!

31:18.920 --> 31:21.575
We don't need all of that, man.
I ain't getting on no ground!

31:21.749 --> 31:24.447
Man 2: I told you to get on--
- I ain't getting on no ground!

31:24.621 --> 31:26.406
Man 2: Get on the ground!
- I ain't getting on no ground!

31:26.580 --> 31:27.581
- Get on the ground!
- Taser!

31:27.755 --> 31:29.322
[electricity crackling]

31:49.559 --> 31:51.431
[door buzzing]

31:52.998 --> 31:54.173
[door shuts]

31:54.347 --> 31:57.089
Fox! Let's go.

31:58.177 --> 31:59.395
You made bail.

32:12.974 --> 32:15.672
Look, maybe you ain't hear me
the first time, alright?

32:15.846 --> 32:18.023
I don't need your help.

32:18.197 --> 32:20.373
Pastor Hood felt bad
about what happened yesterday.

32:20.547 --> 32:22.288
He feels like we may have
blindsided you,

32:22.462 --> 32:23.767
whatever that means.

32:23.942 --> 32:25.378
So when he found out
you were arrested,

32:25.552 --> 32:27.554
he took the money
that the church had raised to--

32:27.728 --> 32:29.817
Tell him I'll pay him back,
alright?

32:29.991 --> 32:31.862
But I'm not working
on your center.

32:32.037 --> 32:33.952
Do you army boys drink coffee?

32:34.126 --> 32:35.649
What?

32:35.823 --> 32:38.478
Listen, this one cup of coffee
isn't gonna ruin

32:38.652 --> 32:41.611
this whole tough-guy thing
you have going on, okay?

32:41.785 --> 32:44.005
Here, you need it.

32:44.179 --> 32:46.268
And plus, there's something
I wanna show you.

32:49.880 --> 32:52.796
[train horn blaring]

33:07.942 --> 33:09.509
What's all this?

33:09.683 --> 33:11.728
You see those men over there?

33:11.902 --> 33:14.949
They were once just like you.

33:15.123 --> 33:18.518
Dedicated, committed,
tough as nails,

33:18.692 --> 33:20.476
they served their country.

33:21.912 --> 33:25.351
And now they're homeless
and troubled.

33:25.525 --> 33:27.266
That's not the military's fault,
Tiffany.

33:27.440 --> 33:29.050
And I never said that it was.

33:29.224 --> 33:31.792
But it doesn't change the fact
that these men

33:31.966 --> 33:35.056
fought for their country,
and now look at them,

33:35.230 --> 33:37.363
sitting over there, hungry,

33:37.537 --> 33:40.061
having no clue where
their next meal will come from.

33:43.934 --> 33:46.502
Travis: So I help you, and these
men get in to your center.

33:48.983 --> 33:49.940
Yes.

33:54.989 --> 33:56.121
[door opens]

33:56.295 --> 33:57.818
Thank you.

33:57.992 --> 34:02.388
[sighs] So, this is where
we meet twice a week.

34:02.562 --> 34:07.045
And as you could see, it can use
a couple of coats of paint.

34:07.219 --> 34:08.698
It needs more then paint, doc.

34:08.872 --> 34:10.657
[chuckles] Pedie, this is...

34:10.831 --> 34:13.225
- How you doing, ranger?
- How you doin'?

34:13.399 --> 34:15.314
Okay, wait.
Have, have you guys already met?

34:15.488 --> 34:17.664
Nope, but I know a ranger
when I see one.

34:17.838 --> 34:19.579
3rd Batt.,
Fort Benning, Georgia.

34:19.753 --> 34:22.016
2nd Batt.,
Fort Lewis, Washington.

34:22.190 --> 34:24.845
- You here to fix this place up?
- Hoo-ah.

34:25.019 --> 34:28.022
- Hoo-ah.
- Hoo-ah.

34:28.196 --> 34:31.547
- Hoo-ah.
- Hoo-ah.

34:31.721 --> 34:33.767
♪ That's a wicked way
for cold for my eye ♪

34:33.941 --> 34:37.640
♪ Praise to the Most High
for the stake of my life ♪

34:37.814 --> 34:39.990
♪ He brushed my teeth
proceeds to the grind ♪

34:40.165 --> 34:42.906
♪ Dream big too big to remind
and live by ♪

34:43.081 --> 34:46.127
♪ Easier said than done that's
why I became more savage ♪

34:46.301 --> 34:48.521
♪ Some shoot for the stars
some will ask for nothing ♪

34:48.695 --> 34:50.131
♪ Level space shadow ♪♪♪

34:50.305 --> 34:52.046
Yo, yo, where you think
you're going?

34:52.220 --> 34:53.787
- I need to talk to Big Six.
- You don't run up in here.

34:53.961 --> 34:55.832
Like you run this place.

34:56.006 --> 34:57.138
Get out of here.

35:00.185 --> 35:01.447
Let him in, D.

35:05.755 --> 35:08.236
Sweat Suit.

35:08.410 --> 35:10.934
Dude, you sent him
to my parents' house?

35:11.109 --> 35:14.068
You got to understand, Donnie,
man, in my line of work,

35:14.242 --> 35:17.071
there are certain insurances
that need to be put into place.

35:17.245 --> 35:20.422
D-- don't you ever send someone
to my parents' house ever again!

35:22.642 --> 35:24.861
So now you gonna come up
in my spot

35:25.035 --> 35:28.430
and tell me what I can
and what I can't do, huh?

35:28.604 --> 35:32.869
- Listen, man, just--
- Shut up! Alright?

35:33.043 --> 35:36.134
Now, listen to me, this how
this gonna go down, alright?

35:36.308 --> 35:39.963
If you don't have my money,
I'm gonna kill you, man.

35:40.138 --> 35:42.836
I'mma kill your pops,
I'mma kill your moms,

35:43.010 --> 35:44.490
I'mma kill whoever.

35:44.664 --> 35:46.056
They gonna get touched!

35:46.231 --> 35:49.930
Gone! Just like that.

35:50.104 --> 35:51.540
Or maybe I'll have Big Damon
here show up at your

35:51.714 --> 35:54.674
family reunion and knock
your whole family off.

35:54.848 --> 35:57.067
♪ One-five-nine ♪

35:57.242 --> 35:58.634
You know I'll do it.

35:58.808 --> 36:01.463
[rap song]

36:01.637 --> 36:04.031
So, Donnie, man, please,
next time I see you,

36:04.205 --> 36:05.728
just have my money, man.

36:09.732 --> 36:11.865
♪ But they rather
see me bust in... ♪♪♪

36:15.434 --> 36:18.306
[engine revving]

36:29.796 --> 36:33.452
- Hey, hey, how's it going?
- Hey. It's good.

36:33.626 --> 36:36.803
You know, I have never seen
Pedie so energized.

36:36.977 --> 36:39.849
These last couple of days
have been amazing.

36:40.023 --> 36:41.373
- It's cool.
- You...

36:41.547 --> 36:42.548
We're about to start a meeting,

36:42.722 --> 36:45.594
you're more than welcome
to stay.

36:45.768 --> 36:48.380
Nah. No,
I got somewhere I got to be.

36:48.554 --> 36:52.079
Okay. You're welcome any time.
[chuckles]

37:00.870 --> 37:02.394
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes, sir?

37:02.568 --> 37:05.832
Do you know where I can find
a Detective Davies?

37:06.006 --> 37:07.486
- She over there.
- Right here?

37:07.660 --> 37:09.314
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

37:11.098 --> 37:13.318
Detective Davies.

37:13.492 --> 37:14.971
A moment of your time.

37:15.145 --> 37:18.453
- Mr. Fox, right?
- Yeah. Yeah, listen.

37:18.627 --> 37:21.326
The necklace in this photo,
my mother never take it off.

37:21.500 --> 37:23.415
When her stuff came back
from the coroner's office,

37:23.589 --> 37:25.765
it wasn't there.
Did you keep it for evidence?

37:25.939 --> 37:27.941
I was responsible for collecting
all the evidence

37:28.115 --> 37:30.422
from the crime scene
and from the coroner.

37:30.596 --> 37:32.337
And that necklace
was never there.

37:32.511 --> 37:35.470
- Maybe you missed it?
- Nope. Didn't miss it.

37:35.644 --> 37:36.819
It wasn't there.

37:39.213 --> 37:41.389
Look, your report said
that there were no witnesses

37:41.563 --> 37:43.391
at the time of the accident
either,

37:43.565 --> 37:46.307
but I was on that street,
the same time as the accident,

37:46.481 --> 37:48.266
and there were lights on
in some of those buildings.

37:48.440 --> 37:50.616
There are some apartments
over some of the shops,

37:50.790 --> 37:53.880
but we talked to everybody,
and no one saw anything.

37:54.054 --> 37:56.230
What they heard was consistent
with the accident report.

37:56.404 --> 37:57.927
My father
would not have accelerated

37:58.101 --> 38:00.060
into a parked city truck,
detective.

38:00.234 --> 38:01.714
It was bad weather.

38:01.888 --> 38:04.107
Perhaps he swerved
to avoid hitting something,

38:04.282 --> 38:05.587
most likely an animal.

38:05.761 --> 38:08.111
He wouldn't have done that,
detective!

38:08.286 --> 38:10.157
Alright, he might have slammed
on the brakes, maybe, alright?

38:10.331 --> 38:12.072
But he would not have
accelerated!

38:12.246 --> 38:14.248
You need to calm down, sir.

38:14.422 --> 38:16.381
Look, we're all very sorry about
what happened to your parents,

38:16.555 --> 38:18.861
but there are no conspiracies,
there are no cover-ups.

38:19.035 --> 38:21.473
It was just
an unfortunate accident.

38:24.650 --> 38:27.348
You wrong, detective.

38:27.522 --> 38:31.744
It was unfortunate,
but it wasn't no accident.

38:35.269 --> 38:37.097
Hood: Can I just talk to you
a little bit this morning?

38:38.794 --> 38:41.014
Second Timothy 2 and 1 tells us

38:41.188 --> 38:43.756
that we must be strong
in the grace

38:43.930 --> 38:46.802
that is in Christ Jesus.

38:46.976 --> 38:49.675
Not be strong in His grace
in the worst of times.

38:52.112 --> 38:54.244
If we claim to be strong
in faith

38:54.419 --> 38:57.770
and know that we are stronger
than others,

38:57.944 --> 38:59.989
I ask you, what should we do?

39:00.163 --> 39:02.949
Should we bear
with the failings of the weak?

39:03.123 --> 39:06.692
Should we bear with those
who are troubled and alone?

39:09.303 --> 39:12.132
Do you, who are strong
in your walk with God,

39:12.306 --> 39:16.179
know that He wants us to work
endlessly, exhaustively,

39:16.354 --> 39:19.400
to help those that are in need
of finding their way to Him?

39:19.574 --> 39:22.185
Carry each other's burdens,

39:22.360 --> 39:25.319
and in this way we will fulfill
the law of Christ.

39:27.539 --> 39:29.497
The Bible says
that no one can come to me

39:29.671 --> 39:32.935
unless the one who sent me
brings you and leads you.

39:33.109 --> 39:36.374
He says, "All that seeks Him
will find Him."

39:38.506 --> 39:42.336
But we that seek Him must seek
Him for the right reasons.

39:44.077 --> 39:46.340
Right?

39:46.514 --> 39:49.996
We must not seek Him just
for forgiveness of our sins.

39:50.170 --> 39:53.216
We must seek Him
by seeking His presence.

39:53.391 --> 39:56.437
For whoever conceals
his transgressions

39:56.611 --> 39:59.397
will not prosper.

39:59.571 --> 40:01.529
But he who walks away from them

40:01.703 --> 40:04.576
will obtain
His grace and mercy.

40:05.925 --> 40:07.666
Amen.

40:07.840 --> 40:08.928
Thank you, Jesus.

40:10.582 --> 40:12.235
[chuckling]

40:12.410 --> 40:16.370
It is time for a break.

40:16.544 --> 40:18.851
Oh, it's cool. Thank you.

40:19.025 --> 40:22.028
- You are very, very welcome.
- Appreciate it.

40:23.246 --> 40:24.683
Mm...

40:26.032 --> 40:27.599
So what's your story?

40:28.600 --> 40:30.819
What do you mean?

40:30.993 --> 40:34.867
You know, how does a doctor
go to selling insurance?

40:35.041 --> 40:37.130
Um, I'm still a doctor

40:37.304 --> 40:41.961
and I do a lot more
than just sell insurance.

40:42.135 --> 40:44.442
But that's another story
for another day.

40:44.616 --> 40:47.140
- How are the repairs coming?
- It's good. It's good.

40:47.314 --> 40:49.142
The parts for the AC came in.

40:49.316 --> 40:51.057
- I'll put 'em on later and...
Tiffany: Okay.

40:51.231 --> 40:52.667
That's pretty much
all I can do until

40:52.841 --> 40:54.495
the church can get
the rest of the supplies.

40:54.669 --> 40:57.629
Great, so I can tell Pastor Hood
that the three homeless vets

40:57.803 --> 40:59.413
can move in
at the end of the week?

40:59.587 --> 41:01.807
- Yeah.
- Good.

41:01.981 --> 41:03.896
What about the money
for the other repairs?

41:04.070 --> 41:07.334
Oh, I'm working on a plan.
[chuckles]

41:09.554 --> 41:11.469
You know, um,

41:11.643 --> 41:15.124
the guys are really gonna miss
having you around here.

41:16.256 --> 41:17.475
They have you.

41:19.955 --> 41:22.610
[sighs] You know,

41:22.784 --> 41:27.093
I heard that army men
really like coffee.

41:27.267 --> 41:29.965
Really? That line again?

41:30.139 --> 41:32.794
I mean, it worked
the first time, didn't it?

41:32.968 --> 41:35.710
So are you gonna join me
for a cup of coffee later?

41:37.886 --> 41:39.975
Yeah, sure. Why not?

41:40.149 --> 41:41.890
But this time
I get to pick the place.

41:42.064 --> 41:43.022
Done.

41:46.547 --> 41:47.417
[Tiffany laughing]

41:47.592 --> 41:49.202
[Travis laughing]

41:49.376 --> 41:52.466
Well, no one told me the
beautiful Dr. Tiffany was here.

41:52.640 --> 41:54.337
Oh. Hey, Pops.

41:54.512 --> 41:55.948
Well, you never told me
you knew Pops.

41:56.122 --> 41:58.385
Um, everybody knows Pops
in this town.

41:58.559 --> 42:01.127
Plus, he comes down
to the center and brings coffee

42:01.301 --> 42:04.304
and pastries for the veterans
every Wednesday.

42:04.478 --> 42:08.047
Hm. It's fine work you're doing
with those boys, Dr. Tiffany.

42:08.221 --> 42:10.745
- Godly work.
Tiffany: Thank you.

42:10.919 --> 42:14.444
I ran into Dr. Cunningham,
she said you paid her a visit.

42:14.619 --> 42:17.056
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, everything's fine.

42:17.230 --> 42:20.929
I was just checking on something
that belonged to my mother.

42:21.103 --> 42:23.715
What's up, man? I've been
looking all over for you.

42:23.889 --> 42:25.499
You don't answer your phone.
How's it going, Pops?

42:25.673 --> 42:27.022
- Hey.
- Hey, Donnie.

42:27.196 --> 42:29.198
- How are you, Tiff?
- Uh-uh, no, you don't.

42:29.372 --> 42:31.592
We have to get ready
to close up for the night.

42:31.766 --> 42:33.638
Doctor, I'll see you Wednesday,
Travis, I'll see you

42:33.812 --> 42:35.509
when I see you. Donnie, come on.

42:35.683 --> 42:37.729
I wanna get home
at a reasonable hour.

42:37.903 --> 42:39.295
Later, Pops.

42:39.469 --> 42:41.341
Hey, man.
I wanna shoot some pool.

42:41.515 --> 42:43.604
You feel like losing some of
that piggy bank money of yours?

42:43.778 --> 42:48.043
Oh, man. I'm tired, brother.
I don't know about tonight, man.

42:48.217 --> 42:50.480
Donnie: Come on, man. You know
a little fun never crush you.

42:50.655 --> 42:52.700
That's what I've been trying
to tell him.

42:52.874 --> 42:54.223
Donnie: Come on!

42:56.095 --> 42:58.271
Alright, brother, I'll meet you
down there at 1900.

42:58.445 --> 43:01.448
Alright. Okay, wait, 1900,
that's 12, 7 p.m.!

43:01.622 --> 43:02.884
Got it. Alright, alright.

43:03.058 --> 43:05.017
- Hey, Donnie.
Donnie: Hey.

43:05.191 --> 43:06.279
Hey, did you ever help
Pops take care of my

43:06.453 --> 43:07.454
parents' place while I was gone?

43:07.628 --> 43:09.195
Yeah. A few times. Why?

43:09.369 --> 43:10.979
Did you ever see this necklace,

43:11.153 --> 43:13.460
this burgundy surrounded
by white gold on all sides?

43:13.634 --> 43:16.506
Ah, nope.
Never seen any necklaces.

43:16.681 --> 43:19.031
- Sorry.
Travis: Alright, man.

43:19.205 --> 43:21.250
Why are you looking
for your mom's necklace?

43:21.424 --> 43:23.470
I gave it to her
right before the accident.

43:23.644 --> 43:25.211
She said she'd never
take it off until

43:25.385 --> 43:27.735
either the war was over
or I never had to go back

43:27.909 --> 43:31.260
and fight no more.
But I can't find it anywhere.

43:31.434 --> 43:35.090
Uh-huh! That's why you were
at the coroner's office.

43:35.264 --> 43:37.745
And the police department,
the fire department,

43:37.919 --> 43:40.618
the ambulance drivers, both of
them, I talked to them, nothing.

43:40.792 --> 43:43.142
Go back to the street,
the apartments, the folks

43:43.316 --> 43:45.971
who live in them above, like
the shops over there, nothing.

43:46.145 --> 43:47.973
Nobody knows anything about it.

43:48.147 --> 43:50.149
Well,
maybe she wasn't wearing it.

43:50.323 --> 43:54.153
Then it would be at the house
somewhere, or her room.

43:54.327 --> 43:57.373
No, I'm pretty sure
she was wearing it.

43:57.547 --> 44:00.028
So, like, you're answering
my question or what?

44:00.202 --> 44:03.118
Okay, okay, so I got my PhD
in clinical psychology

44:03.292 --> 44:05.773
and I had my own practice
for three years,

44:05.947 --> 44:07.862
then, you know,
it just wasn't enough.

44:08.036 --> 44:10.299
So I moved in
to financial planning,

44:10.473 --> 44:11.692
and I never looked back.

44:11.866 --> 44:13.041
And what about the stuff you do

44:13.215 --> 44:14.695
at the center
and at the church?

44:14.869 --> 44:17.132
Well, God has always been
a huge part of my life.

44:17.306 --> 44:18.830
That's how I've made it
this far,

44:19.004 --> 44:22.616
through prayer and His mercy
and His grace, you know?

44:22.790 --> 44:26.489
And the PhD allows me to do
what I love with the guys

44:26.664 --> 44:31.277
at the center, so I have
the best of both worlds.

44:31.451 --> 44:32.626
Okay.

44:34.454 --> 44:35.673
You know...

44:37.326 --> 44:38.937
this is my first date

44:39.111 --> 44:41.287
since moving to town.

44:41.461 --> 44:42.941
This was a date?

44:44.682 --> 44:46.771
- Ha-ha-ha...
- Okay.

44:46.945 --> 44:48.337
Do you remember when I said

44:48.511 --> 44:51.514
the guys at the center
are gonna miss you?

44:51.689 --> 44:54.169
- Yeah.
- Well, I'm gonna miss you, too.

44:56.084 --> 44:58.608
So I have to go grocery shopping
tomorrow.

44:58.783 --> 45:02.395
We need a few things for the
center. Do you wanna come with?

45:05.180 --> 45:07.095
Why not?

45:07.269 --> 45:08.618
- That's another date, huh?
- Yeah.

45:08.793 --> 45:10.708
[both laughing]

45:13.580 --> 45:15.582
See you tomorrow?

45:15.756 --> 45:16.844
- Okay.
- Yup.

45:18.106 --> 45:19.629
[chuckling]

45:19.804 --> 45:21.283
[indistinct chatter]

45:21.457 --> 45:23.155
Boom. Hoo-ah.

45:23.329 --> 45:24.809
If I didn't know any better,
I think you hustled me.

45:24.983 --> 45:26.898
Hoo-ah. [laughing]

45:27.072 --> 45:28.290
Remember, you asked for this,
boy.

45:28.464 --> 45:29.422
Listen, we'll rack them again,
man.

45:29.596 --> 45:32.338
I'm not gonna lose six in a row.

45:32.512 --> 45:34.079
Well, you lost that one.
You rack.

45:34.253 --> 45:36.037
I gotta take a head call.

45:36.211 --> 45:38.953
Lose your rack,
you lose your rack.

45:44.916 --> 45:47.483
- This clown, man.
- Right.

45:49.529 --> 45:51.400
[intense music]

45:51.574 --> 45:52.706
Get the money.

45:52.880 --> 45:54.664
- Let me go check him.
- Yup.

45:56.188 --> 45:57.493
You know what it is.

45:59.321 --> 46:02.281
Suit, Suit, Suit.

46:04.283 --> 46:08.243
It must be a recess time
or something.

46:08.417 --> 46:11.159
- What's going on, Big Six?
- My money, Donnie.

46:11.333 --> 46:13.858
That's what's up.
Where that, though?

46:14.032 --> 46:16.034
I mean, you here playing games,
so that means you must have it.

46:16.208 --> 46:17.992
- Right?
- Look, believe what you want.

46:18.166 --> 46:20.255
Okay, I'll get your money.
I said I will, okay?

46:20.429 --> 46:22.301
First off,
watch how you talk to me.

46:22.475 --> 46:24.782
Secondly, I know you gonna
get it, because if you don't...

46:24.956 --> 46:27.393
- You already know what's gon--
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

46:27.567 --> 46:29.612
Everything good in here, man?

46:29.787 --> 46:31.005
Who is you?

46:31.963 --> 46:33.181
Who are you?

46:35.314 --> 46:36.750
Is this your man?

46:37.882 --> 46:40.362
[laughing] Oh, okay.

46:42.538 --> 46:45.324
War hero, in the flesh.

46:47.456 --> 46:48.893
Do you know who I am?

46:50.242 --> 46:51.460
Should I care?

46:52.984 --> 46:54.855
Okay.

46:55.029 --> 46:58.250
Heard a lot of things
about you, army boy.

46:58.424 --> 47:00.078
Heard you got skills.

47:00.252 --> 47:02.558
You capable of handling yourself
real well.

47:04.647 --> 47:06.258
Put your quarter
on the table, man.

47:06.432 --> 47:08.303
I'll show you how capable I am.

47:10.044 --> 47:11.916
Do I look like I play games,
son?

47:13.395 --> 47:15.310
Look right here, man.

47:15.484 --> 47:17.747
I'm the big dawg
in this town now.

47:17.922 --> 47:19.097
You might need to know that
for the future

47:19.271 --> 47:21.882
and for your personal safety,

47:22.056 --> 47:23.666
if you know what I mean.

47:23.841 --> 47:26.408
- The big dawg.
- Yeah.

47:26.582 --> 47:28.715
Yeah. Alright, ladies,
the door is that way.

47:28.889 --> 47:31.022
- Come on, man.
- Ha-ha-ha...

47:31.196 --> 47:35.069
Army boy got a set on him.
I like that.

47:35.243 --> 47:36.375
Respect.

47:37.289 --> 47:39.160
I'm impressed.

47:39.334 --> 47:41.684
Takes a lot to impress me,
Donnie, I'll tell you that.

47:44.122 --> 47:45.775
Look, man,
maybe we can use somebody

47:45.950 --> 47:49.040
with your special skill set,
uh, down in my organization.

47:49.214 --> 47:52.043
- Not interested.
- You need to be.

47:53.914 --> 47:55.742
Okay. Well, well, what's that?

47:55.916 --> 47:58.310
Oh, you tough now, huh?

47:58.484 --> 48:00.138
See, that's the problem
nowadays.

48:00.312 --> 48:02.140
Any idiot,
no matter how stupid they are,

48:02.314 --> 48:04.359
can get their hands on a gun.

48:04.533 --> 48:05.839
You wanna walk around
like you the tough guy

48:06.013 --> 48:08.102
on the block.

48:08.276 --> 48:10.496
But you wanna impress me,

48:10.670 --> 48:13.064
raise your right hand,
say I do,

48:13.238 --> 48:15.066
strap on the uniform,

48:15.240 --> 48:16.676
then head down range
to face the enemy

48:16.850 --> 48:19.200
that lives to only kill
or capture you

48:19.374 --> 48:21.811
and parades your final moments
on camera...

48:23.117 --> 48:24.945
for the whole world to see.

48:27.295 --> 48:30.603
Look, I've been living dead
for the last 12 years.

48:30.777 --> 48:32.431
No reason to live another day
if you think your boy here

48:32.605 --> 48:34.302
can end my misery.

48:34.476 --> 48:37.262
You think you can do that,
big guy?

48:37.436 --> 48:40.743
I'mma give you a try.
You got one time.

48:40.918 --> 48:43.485
If you think you can get that
gun before I take it from you

48:43.659 --> 48:44.791
and shove it down your throat--

48:44.965 --> 48:47.489
Whoa, whoa, hold on, hold on, D.

48:47.663 --> 48:50.101
We don't wanna smoke while
all these people are here, man.

48:50.275 --> 48:52.799
That's what I thought.

48:52.973 --> 48:57.717
Now, if you girls will excuse
us, we gonna finish our game.

48:57.891 --> 48:58.936
[laughing]

49:00.763 --> 49:02.243
Okay.

49:02.417 --> 49:04.985
Alright, I like that.
I like that, army boy.

49:05.159 --> 49:08.206
Look at here,
you have a change of heart,

49:08.380 --> 49:09.903
you wanna put those skills
of yours to use,

49:10.077 --> 49:13.689
earn some real money,
you come hollering at me.

49:13.863 --> 49:17.476
I ain't hard to find.
I eat lunches here every day.

49:17.650 --> 49:20.000
I know they don't open at 4:00,
but they do a special

49:20.174 --> 49:21.915
private lunch for me.

49:22.089 --> 49:24.439
And it's all free.

49:24.613 --> 49:25.745
You know what I'm saying?

49:25.919 --> 49:27.138
So you come see me
just to show you

49:27.312 --> 49:30.619
there ain't no... love lost,
alright?

49:30.793 --> 49:32.143
Are we done?

49:33.057 --> 49:34.797
Yeah, for now.

49:36.799 --> 49:38.410
Have my money, Donnie.

49:40.020 --> 49:41.674
See you later, army boy.

49:48.811 --> 49:53.164
You got yourself into something
we need to talk about, Donnie?

49:53.338 --> 49:56.297
No, not at all, man.
Let's just, uh, let's just play.

50:00.127 --> 50:01.172
Travis: Why is it so hot
out here, man?

50:01.346 --> 50:03.652
Tiffany: I know.
Oh, my goodness.

50:03.826 --> 50:05.263
Travis: Ah, you picked
the hottest day of the year

50:05.437 --> 50:08.527
to go shopping.
Sweating through my shirt.

50:11.182 --> 50:13.706
Oh. Hoo!

50:13.880 --> 50:15.708
Okay, I hope
I didn't forget anything.

50:15.882 --> 50:17.666
Seriously?
You bought the whole store.

50:17.840 --> 50:19.320
I don't think
you forgot nothing.

50:19.494 --> 50:21.148
Oh, did I get
Marine Corp Bob's peanuts?

50:21.322 --> 50:22.845
Because he loves it.

50:23.020 --> 50:25.196
Peanuts! Oh.
And then what about the--

50:25.370 --> 50:26.371
[dramatic music]

50:26.545 --> 50:27.589
Oh, oh.

50:28.895 --> 50:30.984
Travis?

50:31.158 --> 50:32.029
[baby bawling]

50:32.203 --> 50:33.639
Shut that baby up!

50:35.162 --> 50:36.381
Somebody shut that baby up,

50:36.555 --> 50:37.512
it's gonna give away
our position!

50:37.686 --> 50:38.557
Okay, listen, Travis. Travis.

50:38.731 --> 50:39.688
Travis, listen to me.

50:39.862 --> 50:41.386
There is no, there's no baby.

50:41.560 --> 50:43.040
- There's no baby.
- Get away from me!

50:43.214 --> 50:45.390
Okay, listen, let me help you.

50:45.564 --> 50:47.087
- I don't need nobody's help!
- Okay, listen.

50:47.261 --> 50:49.698
At least, if you won't let me
help you, Travis,

50:49.872 --> 50:51.787
please, let God help you!

50:51.961 --> 50:54.964
Go talk to Pastor Hood because
you cannot do this by yourself.

50:55.139 --> 50:56.488
And if you try,
you are gonna die,

50:56.662 --> 50:57.967
and I cannot let that happen.

50:58.142 --> 50:59.012
Just stay away from me, alright?

50:59.186 --> 51:00.448
Just stay away from me.

51:00.622 --> 51:02.320
- Travis?
- Just stay away from me.

51:04.539 --> 51:07.368
Preach: Travis.
Travis, help me.

51:09.153 --> 51:11.068
Please help me. Travis!

51:11.242 --> 51:14.114
[ominous music]

51:17.944 --> 51:18.901
This is all your fault.

51:19.076 --> 51:20.468
Oh, no!

51:26.257 --> 51:27.736
Come on, man.

51:29.260 --> 51:32.132
[sobbing]

51:36.789 --> 51:38.834
[rain pattering]

51:39.008 --> 51:41.924
[thunder rumbling]

51:48.496 --> 51:51.151
[thunder rumbling]

51:53.762 --> 51:56.635
[instrumental music]

51:58.245 --> 51:59.638
Who's there?

52:03.337 --> 52:05.122
Who's... Travis?

52:07.211 --> 52:08.734
Travis, is that you?

52:12.172 --> 52:14.043
[thunder rumbling]

52:14.218 --> 52:15.915
Here you go, bud.

52:16.089 --> 52:18.613
[sniffles] Thank you.

52:26.926 --> 52:28.797
So what were you doing
out there?

52:32.714 --> 52:34.673
Just considering my options.

52:37.589 --> 52:38.894
What does that mean?

52:40.940 --> 52:42.376
I came here tonight...

52:44.117 --> 52:46.163
'cause I can't live with myself
anymore.

52:48.687 --> 52:50.297
Of what I've become.

52:52.343 --> 52:54.823
- Travis, I know it seems--
- No, pastor, please.

52:55.868 --> 52:57.217
Let me finish.

53:01.569 --> 53:03.789
You know, people think
we keep going back

53:03.963 --> 53:07.967
because we need the adrenaline
and we like killing.

53:10.056 --> 53:11.492
None of that's true.

53:14.060 --> 53:15.931
You know why we keep going back?

53:17.585 --> 53:19.065
Tell me, son.

53:21.415 --> 53:24.418
We go back so we can keep
our brothers and sisters alive.

53:25.724 --> 53:27.726
That's why.

53:27.900 --> 53:31.164
Just the thought
that they are over there

53:31.338 --> 53:33.210
in the, in the fight
without you...

53:34.820 --> 53:36.691
that eats at your soul.

53:39.607 --> 53:41.130
Travis: Now, you start
believing you're the only ones

53:41.305 --> 53:43.132
that can keep them alive.

53:43.307 --> 53:44.830
But then you find out
that that's not true either

53:45.004 --> 53:47.485
because they still die,

53:47.659 --> 53:49.356
just like my friend Preach.

53:50.966 --> 53:52.490
His last mission...

53:57.495 --> 53:59.018
It was hot outside the wire
that night.

53:59.192 --> 54:00.802
[gunfire]

54:00.976 --> 54:02.848
Preach was scared, man.

54:05.546 --> 54:07.548
I've never seen him so afraid.

54:10.421 --> 54:12.336
So he asked me to pray with him.

54:14.076 --> 54:16.122
That's all he wanted.

54:16.296 --> 54:19.343
But I didn't. I didn't do it.

54:21.040 --> 54:23.172
I wouldn't.

54:23.347 --> 54:26.567
That's all that man wanted
was for me to pray with him.

54:26.741 --> 54:30.005
That's all I had to do,
is pray with the man,

54:30.179 --> 54:32.443
but I said no.

54:32.617 --> 54:34.749
Why didn't I just pray
with the man, pastor?

54:37.230 --> 54:39.232
Travis, I'm sure that

54:39.406 --> 54:41.060
your friend understands
why you didn't pray.

54:41.234 --> 54:42.670
He died!

54:45.282 --> 54:47.284
[sniffles] That's what
I understand, pastor, he died,

54:47.458 --> 54:51.853
all of 'em, 35 men, ambushed.

54:55.944 --> 54:58.512
Travis, I have never served
in the military...

55:01.776 --> 55:05.345
so I'm not going to sit here
and pretend

55:05.519 --> 55:09.784
to even... possibly relate

55:09.958 --> 55:11.917
to the hell
that you've been through.

55:14.180 --> 55:17.183
But I can tell you this, son.

55:17.357 --> 55:22.275
I have seen God
turn tragedies into miracles.

55:22.449 --> 55:25.104
As a Christian,

55:25.278 --> 55:28.281
I believe
we should all believe

55:28.455 --> 55:31.676
that God's ways
are higher than our ways.

55:31.850 --> 55:33.242
We might not understand
what He's doing,

55:33.417 --> 55:36.028
but He always has a plan.

55:38.726 --> 55:42.382
Hood: I believe God heard
your friend's prayers.

55:42.556 --> 55:46.517
I believe God answered
your friend's prayers.

55:46.691 --> 55:50.695
His prayers for himself
and his prayers for you.

55:52.610 --> 55:55.352
And I also believe, Travis,

55:55.526 --> 55:59.356
that God has a much greater plan
for your life than war.

56:03.490 --> 56:06.014
[sniffles] Man, that's the same
thing he said that night.

56:10.889 --> 56:13.370
I'm not saying any of this
to make you feel better.

56:14.980 --> 56:17.112
I'm saying it
because I believe it.

56:18.766 --> 56:21.421
Preach used to always say,

56:21.595 --> 56:23.031
he said, "Travis...

56:29.124 --> 56:30.648
don't leave this Earth...

56:34.391 --> 56:36.871
without making sure
your soul is ready."

56:41.267 --> 56:43.138
But I don't know
when I'm leaving this Earth.

56:45.184 --> 56:47.055
But I know my soul ain't ready.

56:49.623 --> 56:50.537
No.

56:54.715 --> 56:56.761
I'm gonna read you something
out of this book...

56:58.893 --> 57:00.765
that you've probably
heard before.

57:09.600 --> 57:11.732
"Who is it
that overcomes the world?"

57:14.169 --> 57:17.172
"Only he who believes
that Jesus is the Son of God."

57:24.615 --> 57:29.489
Travis, I know you were baptized
as a child,

57:29.663 --> 57:32.100
but the Bible says,
"He who believes

57:32.274 --> 57:35.452
and is baptized will be saved."

57:44.025 --> 57:46.158
I don't know if I'm ready
for all that yet.

57:47.289 --> 57:48.943
I get it.

57:49.117 --> 57:52.730
I'm not asking you
to make that decision tonight,

57:52.904 --> 57:56.864
but I do want you to know
that your faith is gonna grow...

57:58.649 --> 58:01.216
and your trust in the Lord
is gonna grow,

58:01.390 --> 58:04.916
and that trust and that faith is
gonna lead you to that pool...

58:08.441 --> 58:09.747
or one like it.

58:15.753 --> 58:17.450
Well, first
I'd like to say welcome.

58:17.624 --> 58:20.366
I'm so happy that all of you
decided to join us here today.

58:20.540 --> 58:22.977
I wanna remind everyone
that this is a safe space.

58:23.151 --> 58:26.981
This is a space that we share,
that we respect one another

58:27.155 --> 58:29.897
and one another's feelings...

58:31.856 --> 58:33.510
Come on in and join us.

58:34.728 --> 58:36.338
You're right on time.

58:42.562 --> 58:45.217
[sighs] Well,
tonight we're gonna start

58:45.391 --> 58:46.697
with a very simple exercise,

58:46.871 --> 58:49.003
one that many of you
have done before.

58:49.177 --> 58:52.224
I'm really happy
that you, um, you came tonight.

58:53.617 --> 58:56.837
Yeah, me, too. It was different.

58:57.011 --> 58:59.797
[sighs] Pastor Hood told me

58:59.971 --> 59:01.668
about what happened
the other day.

59:03.583 --> 59:05.193
That was different, too.

59:05.367 --> 59:09.154
No. That was God, Travis.

59:09.328 --> 59:11.548
God working His miracles.

59:12.592 --> 59:14.507
- Tiff.
- Yeah?

59:15.856 --> 59:17.554
Talk to you for a second?

59:20.078 --> 59:22.123
- I had a friend.
- Mm-hmm.

59:23.211 --> 59:24.517
Named Preach.

59:25.518 --> 59:27.346
This was his.

59:27.520 --> 59:30.218
He used to say stuff like
what you said all the time.

59:32.438 --> 59:35.049
- You wanna hear about them?
- Of course.

59:35.223 --> 59:36.703
Hood: When the disciples
heard this,

59:36.877 --> 59:39.663
they were greatly astonished
and asked,

59:39.837 --> 59:42.753
"Who then can be saved?"

59:42.927 --> 59:45.233
Jesus answered them and said,

59:45.407 --> 59:48.149
"With man, this is impossible,

59:48.323 --> 59:51.544
but with God,
all things are possible."

59:51.718 --> 59:53.372
Man: Praise God.
All: Amen.

59:53.546 --> 59:57.115
Hood: Praise Jesus. Thank you,
Lord. Thank you, Lord.

59:58.420 --> 59:59.770
Thank you.

59:59.944 --> 1:00:02.468
- God bless you, sir.
- God bless you.

1:00:02.642 --> 1:00:05.297
Well, Deacon Tiffany.

1:00:05.471 --> 1:00:07.734
- Great sermon, pastor.
- Thank you.

1:00:07.908 --> 1:00:10.737
- Travis, it's good to have you.
- It's good to be here.

1:00:10.911 --> 1:00:13.958
It felt really good
to be here today. Enjoyed it.

1:00:14.132 --> 1:00:15.568
I know you've got to report back
for duty soon,

1:00:15.742 --> 1:00:18.963
but I've got a little favor
I wanna ask you.

1:00:19.137 --> 1:00:20.529
What's that, pastor?

1:00:20.704 --> 1:00:22.053
I was wondering
if you might be willing

1:00:22.227 --> 1:00:23.532
to share your testimony

1:00:23.707 --> 1:00:25.360
at Bible study Wednesday night.

1:00:25.534 --> 1:00:26.710
Now, I know it might be
a little soon--

1:00:26.884 --> 1:00:27.972
Nah, I'll do it.

1:00:28.146 --> 1:00:29.713
- Really?
- Yeah, yeah.

1:00:29.887 --> 1:00:32.803
Yeah, I mean, it'd be different,

1:00:32.977 --> 1:00:35.632
but my therapist suggested
that I start talking more,

1:00:35.806 --> 1:00:37.503
you know,
share my feelings, so...

1:00:37.677 --> 1:00:39.374
She's a smart lady.

1:00:39.548 --> 1:00:42.160
Tell you what, maybe that
therapist, whoever she may be,

1:00:42.334 --> 1:00:44.728
might help you find the reason
to come back home

1:00:44.902 --> 1:00:46.338
before another three years
goes by.

1:00:46.512 --> 1:00:49.167
Tiffany: Hm.
- It's just a thought.

1:00:49.341 --> 1:00:51.038
Yeah, maybe.

1:00:53.084 --> 1:00:53.998
Wow.

1:00:55.956 --> 1:00:59.220
You know, I think Preach
would be proud of me right now.

1:00:59.394 --> 1:01:02.223
I think he is very proud of you
right now.

1:01:04.182 --> 1:01:07.402
[chuckles] Let's go.

1:01:09.666 --> 1:01:12.581
[cell phone ringing]

1:01:16.237 --> 1:01:17.456
- Hey, Pops.
Pops: Hello, son.

1:01:17.630 --> 1:01:19.719
Have you seen
Donnie at all today?

1:01:19.893 --> 1:01:22.504
No, actually, I haven't seen
or heard from him all day.

1:01:22.679 --> 1:01:25.029
Pops: Okay.
Uh, can you do me a favor?

1:01:25.203 --> 1:01:27.640
- Sure, yeah, okay.
- Will you check Parkers and--

1:01:27.814 --> 1:01:28.859
I'll talk to the Parkers,
no problem.

1:01:29.033 --> 1:01:30.948
- And give me a call?
- Okay.

1:01:31.122 --> 1:01:32.819
Pops: His poor mother's
worried to death.

1:01:32.993 --> 1:01:33.951
Alright.

1:01:37.737 --> 1:01:39.957
[laughing]

1:01:44.875 --> 1:01:47.747
[chuckles] Well,
you can practice all you want,

1:01:47.921 --> 1:01:49.923
you know,
you'll never be able to...

1:01:51.272 --> 1:01:53.492
Who did that to your face, man?

1:01:53.666 --> 1:01:54.754
- It's not your business.
- Okay, well...

1:01:54.928 --> 1:01:56.800
I'm making it my business.

1:01:59.324 --> 1:02:01.326
Look, I screwed up, man.

1:02:01.500 --> 1:02:04.416
I screwed up real bad
and cost my dad his shop.

1:02:04.590 --> 1:02:06.679
So, what, this Big Six guy,
he taking Pops' money

1:02:06.853 --> 1:02:08.899
'cause of something you did?

1:02:09.073 --> 1:02:10.596
And now there's only one way
out of this.

1:02:10.770 --> 1:02:12.685
How, Donnie?

1:02:12.859 --> 1:02:15.122
Big Six has some cross-town
rival named Suarez,

1:02:15.296 --> 1:02:17.211
who runs the Latino Vice Lords.

1:02:17.385 --> 1:02:18.778
So what does that have to do
with you?

1:02:18.952 --> 1:02:20.737
I don't know,
Suarez has a major drug shipment

1:02:20.911 --> 1:02:23.000
coming in this weekend,
and Big Six found out

1:02:23.174 --> 1:02:24.566
where he's keeping the cash
to pay for the score,

1:02:24.741 --> 1:02:26.177
at his girl's crib
on Station Ave.

1:02:26.351 --> 1:02:29.267
And he wants you
to lift the cash for him?

1:02:29.441 --> 1:02:30.398
Donnie, you can't do that, man.

1:02:30.572 --> 1:02:31.878
Yeah, I told him that last night

1:02:32.052 --> 1:02:34.794
and his goon Damon
wasn't having it.

1:02:34.968 --> 1:02:37.623
Look, listen to me,
you go down to Pops' shop,

1:02:37.797 --> 1:02:40.234
have them close up early today.

1:02:40.408 --> 1:02:41.627
- What?
- Look, Donnie, we both know.

1:02:41.801 --> 1:02:43.455
How this game is played,
alright?

1:02:43.629 --> 1:02:45.239
Go have Pops close early

1:02:45.413 --> 1:02:48.590
and then you go home
and stay there, alright?

1:02:48.765 --> 1:02:50.288
- I'll call you later.
- Well, Travis, wait!

1:02:50.462 --> 1:02:52.551
Go, Donnie!

1:02:52.725 --> 1:02:54.292
I'll take care of it, man.

1:02:55.510 --> 1:02:56.424
- Travis!
Travis: Go!

1:02:56.598 --> 1:02:57.861
Travis!

1:03:03.867 --> 1:03:05.738
Hey, you know we didn't get
a chance to go by that last spot

1:03:05.912 --> 1:03:07.914
and get that money.

1:03:08.088 --> 1:03:10.699
Big Six: We can't take
no more errors, alright?

1:03:10.874 --> 1:03:12.745
Hey, Six, I'll be right back.

1:03:13.702 --> 1:03:16.270
[line ringing]

1:03:16.444 --> 1:03:19.404
Hey, let me get some steaks off.

1:03:19.578 --> 1:03:21.885
- Okay.
- Hey. Yeah.

1:03:22.059 --> 1:03:25.018
No, no, no, I'mma-- I'mma have
the money. I promise.

1:03:25.192 --> 1:03:29.631
You know I'm good for it, man.
Yeah.

1:03:29.806 --> 1:03:32.156
No, no, no, look,
I just, I just got to be...

1:03:37.639 --> 1:03:39.250
Let me call you back.

1:03:42.993 --> 1:03:44.908
He lost his appetite.

1:03:45.952 --> 1:03:47.040
[sniffles]

1:03:47.911 --> 1:03:49.608
[claps]

1:03:49.782 --> 1:03:54.265
Well played, army boy.
Well played.

1:03:54.439 --> 1:03:56.136
Guess he won't be needing this.

1:03:57.921 --> 1:03:59.487
You mind passing me the sugar?

1:03:59.661 --> 1:04:01.663
Well, Donnie won't be lifting
that money for you.

1:04:01.838 --> 1:04:03.970
Well, that little fool
just can't keep

1:04:04.144 --> 1:04:05.580
his mouth shut, now, can he?

1:04:05.754 --> 1:04:08.409
And Pops ain't giving you
no more money.

1:04:08.583 --> 1:04:11.456
Wait, whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa,
look at here now.

1:04:11.630 --> 1:04:13.719
Same thing I told Donnie.

1:04:13.893 --> 1:04:17.114
Everybody pays, alright?

1:04:17.288 --> 1:04:20.073
You go near Donnie again,
you touch Donnie,

1:04:20.247 --> 1:04:23.424
you go near Pops' shop,
I'm coming back.

1:04:23.598 --> 1:04:25.078
And the next time
it won't be your boy out there

1:04:25.252 --> 1:04:27.994
laying in his own blood,
you understand that?

1:04:33.913 --> 1:04:36.437
Hey, army boy.

1:04:36.611 --> 1:04:39.701
Heard you've been asking
a lot of questions around town

1:04:39.876 --> 1:04:43.749
about your parents and their,
um, untimely accident.

1:04:43.923 --> 1:04:45.838
Look, you better be real careful
with the next few words

1:04:46.012 --> 1:04:47.709
that come up out of your mouth.

1:04:47.884 --> 1:04:50.234
Ain't nobody got nothing
to tell you, man.

1:04:51.583 --> 1:04:53.063
But maybe I do.

1:04:53.933 --> 1:04:55.848
[laughs]

1:04:57.154 --> 1:04:58.459
Talk, man.

1:05:00.374 --> 1:05:04.161
No. I'm done talking.

1:05:04.335 --> 1:05:06.206
You wanna hear
what I got to say?

1:05:06.380 --> 1:05:10.080
You already know what you got
to do for me. Alright?

1:05:10.254 --> 1:05:12.125
How do I know you're not lying?

1:05:13.300 --> 1:05:14.998
You don't.

1:05:15.172 --> 1:05:17.130
But what you do wanna know is...

1:05:18.349 --> 1:05:20.090
what really happened that night.

1:05:20.264 --> 1:05:23.136
Ah. [laughs]

1:05:26.357 --> 1:05:28.446
Oh, oh, okay.

1:05:28.620 --> 1:05:30.491
So what, you gonna cut me now?

1:05:30.665 --> 1:05:34.017
Go ahead, army boy,
poke me full of holes.

1:05:34.191 --> 1:05:35.801
But you know what,
everything that I know

1:05:35.975 --> 1:05:37.716
about what really happened
that night

1:05:37.890 --> 1:05:40.414
is gonna bleed out
all over this table.

1:05:45.332 --> 1:05:46.290
Yeah.

1:05:48.379 --> 1:05:50.990
[chuckles] Hey, come on, man.

1:05:51.164 --> 1:05:53.384
Now, that's just disrespectful.

1:05:53.558 --> 1:05:57.040
[chuckles] You're just gonna
ruin my brunch, huh?

1:05:57.214 --> 1:05:58.302
Alright.

1:05:58.476 --> 1:06:00.173
Hey, army boy,

1:06:00.347 --> 1:06:03.481
you wanna know what really
happened, you get me my money.

1:06:04.525 --> 1:06:06.005
[door shuts]

1:06:14.535 --> 1:06:16.537
Travis on phone:
Donnie, it's me.

1:06:16.711 --> 1:06:19.149
Where are you? You okay?
What'd you do?

1:06:19.323 --> 1:06:21.064
He said he knows something
about my parents' accident.

1:06:21.238 --> 1:06:22.891
What? Who, Big Six?

1:06:23.066 --> 1:06:24.676
Yeah, so I'mma have to lift
his money for him.

1:06:24.850 --> 1:06:27.418
Travis, you can't do that!
He's lying, man!

1:06:27.592 --> 1:06:29.028
Look, I done talked to everybody
who knows anything

1:06:29.202 --> 1:06:30.899
about my parents' accident.

1:06:31.074 --> 1:06:33.206
- Ain't got no choice, Donnie.
- He doesn't know nothing!

1:06:33.380 --> 1:06:35.513
Listen, Travis,
stay out of this, okay?

1:06:35.687 --> 1:06:37.602
Big Six is not playing around,
if you steal that money,

1:06:37.776 --> 1:06:39.169
you know exactly
what he's gonna do to you.

1:06:39.343 --> 1:06:41.127
Don't matter,
I ain't got no choice. Look.

1:06:41.301 --> 1:06:42.868
I got something else
I got to do at the church.

1:06:43.042 --> 1:06:45.175
You just stay home
like I told you, alright?

1:06:47.003 --> 1:06:48.743
Travis. Travis!

1:06:53.096 --> 1:06:56.012
[cell phone vibrating]

1:07:05.064 --> 1:07:08.763
Tonight we're gonna
shake things up a little bit.

1:07:08.937 --> 1:07:10.722
Sometimes it's easy for us
to forget

1:07:10.896 --> 1:07:12.898
that real life

1:07:13.072 --> 1:07:16.162
can be really complicated
sometimes.

1:07:17.990 --> 1:07:21.994
So tonight
we are going to be blessed

1:07:22.168 --> 1:07:24.953
by a very powerful testimony.

1:07:25.128 --> 1:07:27.173
So if I have your permission,

1:07:27.347 --> 1:07:29.871
I'm gonna trade places
with Travis,

1:07:30.046 --> 1:07:33.266
and he's gonna come up here
and share his story.

1:07:34.354 --> 1:07:37.227
[applauding]

1:07:40.404 --> 1:07:42.928
- Appreciate it.
- Thank you.

1:07:43.102 --> 1:07:44.060
[clears throat]

1:07:47.367 --> 1:07:51.676
[sighs] Well, uh, good evening,
everybody.

1:07:51.850 --> 1:07:56.072
Um, my name is Sergeant
First Class Travis Fox.

1:07:56.246 --> 1:07:57.203
Wanda on phone: Did Donnie
show up at all?

1:07:57.377 --> 1:07:59.075
Well, no, he never showed up.

1:07:59.249 --> 1:08:02.034
Uh, Travis went looking for him,
but he didn't call me back.

1:08:02.208 --> 1:08:04.515
Wanda: I'm worried, Joe.
- I'm sure he's fine.

1:08:04.689 --> 1:08:06.952
Wanda: Will you be home soon?
- Yeah, I'm locking up now.

1:08:07.126 --> 1:08:09.172
Wanda: I love you.
- Alright, love you, too.

1:08:10.216 --> 1:08:11.565
[gunshots]

1:08:12.784 --> 1:08:14.655
Wanda on phone: Joe?

1:08:14.829 --> 1:08:18.659
Joe? What was that? Joe!

1:08:18.833 --> 1:08:22.489
Look, for a long time
I was using my parents' death

1:08:22.663 --> 1:08:24.361
as a reason to hate God.

1:08:27.015 --> 1:08:30.454
But I realized that's not true.

1:08:30.628 --> 1:08:33.805
I started hating God
a long time ago.

1:08:33.979 --> 1:08:36.764
You see, over the years,

1:08:36.938 --> 1:08:40.203
I've lost a lot of friends
in this war.

1:08:40.377 --> 1:08:41.856
And I don't blame
the government,

1:08:42.030 --> 1:08:44.511
I don't blame the military.

1:08:44.685 --> 1:08:47.732
I mean, we-- we-- we knew
what we were doing.

1:08:47.906 --> 1:08:50.213
We knew where we were going.

1:08:50.387 --> 1:08:52.345
We knew what we was
getting ourselves into.

1:08:54.826 --> 1:08:57.481
We just didn't know...

1:08:57.655 --> 1:09:00.136
what will happen to us
when we came back.

1:09:00.310 --> 1:09:02.268
After all the violence ends...

1:09:03.704 --> 1:09:06.185
certain things stay with you.

1:09:06.359 --> 1:09:10.146
Then you start seeing
the faces of the dead.

1:09:11.625 --> 1:09:13.671
You want it to stop,
but it don't.

1:09:15.107 --> 1:09:17.196
And it happens all the time,

1:09:17.370 --> 1:09:21.766
while you eating,
when you're sleeping.

1:09:21.940 --> 1:09:26.684
Travis: And then you start
thinking about other options...

1:09:28.512 --> 1:09:30.514
'cause you want the pain
to stop.

1:09:32.516 --> 1:09:34.605
And that's when you start
convincing yourself...

1:09:38.261 --> 1:09:41.916
maybe dying is a far better
option than living.

1:09:47.400 --> 1:09:51.535
I was facing that option
last week...

1:09:53.450 --> 1:09:56.496
out there in your parking lot.

1:09:59.020 --> 1:10:00.326
Travis: Live or die.

1:10:04.765 --> 1:10:06.941
And I put my gun on my head.

1:10:16.081 --> 1:10:17.996
[sobbing]

1:10:21.304 --> 1:10:23.131
I put my gun to my head...

1:10:25.133 --> 1:10:27.005
and I said some things to God.

1:10:28.963 --> 1:10:30.356
I thought these would be
the last words

1:10:30.530 --> 1:10:32.750
that I would ever speak
in this lifetime.

1:10:36.014 --> 1:10:37.407
I told him...

1:10:39.626 --> 1:10:43.543
"If you love me
the way Preach said you do,

1:10:43.717 --> 1:10:45.415
you always love me,

1:10:45.589 --> 1:10:49.201
you always good all the time...

1:10:52.204 --> 1:10:53.945
you got to show me."

1:10:56.600 --> 1:10:58.906
"You got to show me
right here, right now."

1:11:03.520 --> 1:11:04.956
"You're gonna show me...

1:11:06.479 --> 1:11:08.568
that I belong to you
and you love me."

1:11:10.353 --> 1:11:12.616
"That I belong to you,
I'm one of yours."

1:11:14.661 --> 1:11:16.228
And I hear nothing.

1:11:18.099 --> 1:11:19.492
I ain't feel nothing.

1:11:22.626 --> 1:11:24.367
So I was about
to pull the trigger.

1:11:27.979 --> 1:11:30.286
That's when the doors
of this church opened...

1:11:32.636 --> 1:11:34.377
and your pastor walked out.

1:11:34.551 --> 1:11:37.423
[instrumental music]

1:11:39.643 --> 1:11:40.731
Look...

1:11:42.907 --> 1:11:45.910
I didn't come here tonight to
tell you all that I'm healed...

1:11:47.390 --> 1:11:48.739
'cause I'm not.

1:11:50.610 --> 1:11:52.525
I have PTSD.

1:11:55.267 --> 1:11:57.835
And there's a long road ahead
for me.

1:11:59.663 --> 1:12:00.925
I know that.

1:12:02.796 --> 1:12:04.798
Well, I'm seeking
medical attention...

1:12:07.627 --> 1:12:09.325
to heal my mind.

1:12:12.719 --> 1:12:14.330
And I'm seeking God...

1:12:16.636 --> 1:12:20.118
to heal my soul, my heart.

1:12:22.120 --> 1:12:23.643
And I'm determined...

1:12:25.776 --> 1:12:27.908
to find my way back to God.

1:12:29.693 --> 1:12:32.565
[applauding]

1:12:40.704 --> 1:12:42.314
- Is this the gunshot victim?
- Yes.

1:12:42.488 --> 1:12:43.489
Room four.

1:12:43.663 --> 1:12:46.536
[siren blaring]

1:12:49.800 --> 1:12:51.976
Hood: Come in here,
all of you who fear God,

1:12:52.150 --> 1:12:55.675
and I will share
what He has done for my soul.

1:12:55.849 --> 1:12:58.374
Son, your words
really moved the house tonight.

1:12:59.331 --> 1:13:00.724
Thank you, pastor.

1:13:00.898 --> 1:13:02.116
Appreciate you
letting me talk to 'em.

1:13:02.290 --> 1:13:04.771
I appreciate you coming.

1:13:04.945 --> 1:13:06.643
Wish I could stay longer,

1:13:06.817 --> 1:13:09.950
but, um, I have something else
I need to do.

1:13:12.257 --> 1:13:14.172
It's Pops.

1:13:14.346 --> 1:13:16.043
Damon: He should be here by now.

1:13:17.654 --> 1:13:19.525
Check it.

1:13:19.699 --> 1:13:22.354
After we handle the war hero,
man,

1:13:22.528 --> 1:13:26.619
I want you to put a call
into them out-of-town guys, man.

1:13:26.793 --> 1:13:30.884
Tell them I wanna take out
Donnie and his mama, too.

1:13:32.886 --> 1:13:34.018
Got it.

1:13:36.847 --> 1:13:39.676
- What happened?
- He was closing the shop.

1:13:39.850 --> 1:13:44.202
We were on the phone together,
then I heard gunshots. [sobbing]

1:13:44.376 --> 1:13:46.465
- Was Donnie there?
- No.

1:13:46.639 --> 1:13:48.598
He didn't show up for work
today.

1:13:48.772 --> 1:13:50.034
Okay.
So what did the doctor say?

1:13:50.208 --> 1:13:52.428
He said the next couple of days

1:13:52.602 --> 1:13:54.386
will determine
if he will make it.

1:13:54.560 --> 1:13:56.344
Don't worry about that,
Ms. Wanda.

1:13:56.519 --> 1:13:59.043
Pops a ranger. He'll make it.

1:14:00.131 --> 1:14:02.220
[intense music]

1:14:02.394 --> 1:14:05.092
- Where did you get that?
- What? What?

1:14:05.266 --> 1:14:07.617
That necklace!
Where did you get that necklace?

1:14:07.791 --> 1:14:09.009
- Travis?
- Donnie.

1:14:09.183 --> 1:14:11.621
Donnie gave me this necklace.
Why?

1:14:13.884 --> 1:14:16.234
Tiffany: Travis!

1:14:16.408 --> 1:14:19.324
Travis! Travis, wait! Please!

1:14:19.498 --> 1:14:21.761
Look, that was my mother's
necklace, alright?

1:14:21.935 --> 1:14:23.676
How did Donnie get
my mother's necklace?

1:14:23.850 --> 1:14:26.505
I don't know,
but please calm down.

1:14:26.679 --> 1:14:29.334
- Uh, I gotta go, alright?
- Travis!

1:14:34.948 --> 1:14:37.821
[cell phone ringing]

1:14:45.655 --> 1:14:47.700
[line ringing]

1:14:47.874 --> 1:14:50.573
Hello, papi,
I think someone's here.

1:14:52.400 --> 1:14:54.446
[siren blaring]

1:14:54.620 --> 1:14:57.493
[dog barking]

1:15:01.235 --> 1:15:03.063
What he waiting on?

1:15:03.237 --> 1:15:07.415
I don't know.
Light's still on, though.

1:15:07.590 --> 1:15:11.419
Yeah, but we out here exposed
on Suarez's turf.

1:15:11.594 --> 1:15:13.987
The longer we sit here,
the longer...

1:15:14.161 --> 1:15:16.860
We alright.
No, no, trust me, we alright.

1:15:17.034 --> 1:15:18.296
All I'm saying is--

1:15:18.470 --> 1:15:21.081
Look, I just said
we alright, okay?

1:15:21.255 --> 1:15:22.909
We gotta get this money, man,

1:15:23.083 --> 1:15:24.476
'cause if we don't get
this money,

1:15:24.650 --> 1:15:26.565
we gonna have to deal
with the connect.

1:15:26.739 --> 1:15:27.958
And you already know
what they gonna do.

1:15:28.132 --> 1:15:29.829
So if you don't wanna deal
with that,

1:15:30.003 --> 1:15:33.833
I suggest you shut up
and stay sharp. Alright?

1:15:44.409 --> 1:15:46.063
Oh, please, wait!

1:15:46.237 --> 1:15:48.631
Travis: Shut up!
- Travis?

1:15:48.805 --> 1:15:50.589
How'd your mother
get my necklace?

1:15:50.763 --> 1:15:51.938
Get what?
What are you talking about?

1:15:52.112 --> 1:15:53.984
Ms. Wanda had
my mother's necklace on!

1:15:54.158 --> 1:15:55.463
- How did you get it?
- I tried to tell you.

1:15:55.638 --> 1:15:56.813
So many times, okay, man,

1:15:56.987 --> 1:15:57.857
but I couldn't tell you that.

1:15:58.031 --> 1:15:59.250
I couldn't. I'm sorry!

1:15:59.424 --> 1:16:01.339
- I'm sorry!
- What happened, man?

1:16:01.513 --> 1:16:02.906
How did you get the necklace,
Donnie?

1:16:03.080 --> 1:16:05.604
Uh, Denzel, okay!

1:16:05.778 --> 1:16:07.824
He wanted to be the Big Six,

1:16:07.998 --> 1:16:10.087
so he made his move
to take over the turf.

1:16:10.261 --> 1:16:11.567
Donnie: He had a secret meet
with the previous Big

1:16:11.741 --> 1:16:13.481
and his two captains.

1:16:13.656 --> 1:16:16.528
A few minutes into the meet,
all I hear is gunfire.

1:16:16.702 --> 1:16:18.530
Denzel comes running
out of the building

1:16:18.704 --> 1:16:21.011
and we run down the alley,
and I ran out of the alley

1:16:21.185 --> 1:16:22.882
and your dad
stepped on the gas,

1:16:23.056 --> 1:16:24.971
swerved
on to someone's vehicle.

1:16:25.145 --> 1:16:26.799
I was looking
right at them, man.

1:16:26.973 --> 1:16:29.497
And they were already gone,
man.

1:16:29.672 --> 1:16:31.630
There was nothing I could do.

1:16:31.804 --> 1:16:34.372
I swear, nothing I could do.
I couldn't believe it.

1:16:34.546 --> 1:16:36.200
Travis: They were my parents,
man!

1:16:36.374 --> 1:16:38.811
Why didn't you just
tell me the truth, man?

1:16:38.985 --> 1:16:41.422
You're supposed to be
my best friend, Donnie.

1:16:41.597 --> 1:16:43.511
You could have came to me!

1:16:46.602 --> 1:16:48.342
I'm sorry, man.

1:16:49.474 --> 1:16:51.258
I'm sorry, man. I'm sorry.

1:16:51.432 --> 1:16:52.782
I couldn't, man. I couldn't.

1:16:52.956 --> 1:16:54.697
Just kill me, man, 'cause...

1:16:55.785 --> 1:16:58.222
I'm dead already.

1:16:58.396 --> 1:16:59.919
And if I don't go
in that house--

1:17:00.093 --> 1:17:01.747
- You ain't going in the house.
- And get that money...

1:17:01.921 --> 1:17:03.140
- You ain't going over there.
- They're gonna kill him.

1:17:03.314 --> 1:17:04.184
- And take my dad's shop.
- Donnie.

1:17:04.358 --> 1:17:05.621
You ain't going in there!

1:17:10.974 --> 1:17:13.498
That's Big Six' whip
right there, man.

1:17:13.672 --> 1:17:14.673
You go in that house
and you gonna die!

1:17:14.847 --> 1:17:16.196
That money is blood money!

1:17:16.370 --> 1:17:18.068
And tonight it's your...

1:17:19.809 --> 1:17:21.637
It's my, it's my what?

1:17:23.726 --> 1:17:25.641
It's your daddy's blood
on that money, man.

1:17:25.815 --> 1:17:27.860
- Man, they shot Pops, man.
- What?

1:17:28.034 --> 1:17:29.732
They tried to kill him!

1:17:29.906 --> 1:17:31.124
And if the game
is still the same,

1:17:31.298 --> 1:17:32.169
you and your mother are next!

1:17:32.343 --> 1:17:33.997
They killed my dad?

1:17:37.827 --> 1:17:39.045
[guns cocking]

1:17:39.219 --> 1:17:40.394
He's still alive, but we got...

1:17:40.568 --> 1:17:42.440
[gunshots]

1:17:42.614 --> 1:17:44.181
We got to go. We got to go.
Come on, let's move.

1:17:44.355 --> 1:17:45.661
Move! Let's go!

1:17:48.272 --> 1:17:50.535
Hey, are you okay?

1:17:50.709 --> 1:17:52.711
You know the answer to that.

1:17:52.885 --> 1:17:55.627
So what happened? How did Donnie
get your mother's necklace?

1:17:55.801 --> 1:17:58.543
- It's not your concern.
- Travis, please.

1:17:58.717 --> 1:18:00.632
Please don't shut me out.

1:18:02.982 --> 1:18:04.854
I know you're never gonna
forgive me, but...

1:18:08.466 --> 1:18:10.250
Travis, please.

1:18:10.424 --> 1:18:13.123
- Travis!
- What, Tiffany?

1:18:13.297 --> 1:18:14.254
Is this the part
where you tell me

1:18:14.428 --> 1:18:16.343
everything's gonna be alright?

1:18:16.517 --> 1:18:17.562
That it's okay
that my best friend

1:18:17.736 --> 1:18:19.477
caused my parents' accident?

1:18:19.651 --> 1:18:20.957
I'm supposed to pray
and everything gonna be alright?

1:18:21.131 --> 1:18:22.132
I don't wanna hear that,
Tiffany.

1:18:22.306 --> 1:18:23.873
- No, but--
- Ain't no buts.

1:18:24.047 --> 1:18:26.789
Tiffany, there's no way
you or nobody else can tell me

1:18:26.963 --> 1:18:29.356
that God cares about me
when all He's ever done

1:18:29.530 --> 1:18:31.141
is take away anybody
who's ever loved

1:18:31.315 --> 1:18:33.709
or cared about me,
so I'm through.

1:18:33.883 --> 1:18:35.580
Not everyone.

1:18:35.754 --> 1:18:39.366
Look, there's no path
back to God for me, alright?

1:18:39.540 --> 1:18:43.240
There's nothing left
but death, lies, hate.

1:18:43.414 --> 1:18:45.068
Look, I'm through, alright?

1:18:45.242 --> 1:18:47.331
- I'm all out of options.
- Travis!

1:18:52.031 --> 1:18:55.556
Hood: Satan is at work
every day,

1:18:55.731 --> 1:18:57.645
trying to keep you away
from the gifts

1:18:57.820 --> 1:18:59.996
and the life
that God has promised you.

1:19:01.171 --> 1:19:03.260
He'll try to keep you down,

1:19:03.434 --> 1:19:06.785
hurt you, depress you,

1:19:06.959 --> 1:19:11.268
even destroy those
who you love and care about.

